WEBVTT

00:12.476 --> 00:14.353
MAN:
<i>Hey! Programs, souvenirs!</i>

00:14.895 --> 00:16.647
<i>Programs, souvenirs!</i>

00:16.980 --> 00:18.023
[♪♪♪]

00:22.152 --> 00:23.403
PLAYER 1:
Okay, I got him.

00:24.488 --> 00:25.739
[PLAYER 2 WHISTLES]

00:27.950 --> 00:29.660
[PLAYERS CHATTERING]

00:34.164 --> 00:37.626
♪ <i>Nobody's hero</i>
<i>But I used to be</i> ♪

00:38.085 --> 00:40.712
♪ <i>That's a ghost</i>
<i>Haunting me</i> ♪

00:40.879 --> 00:43.048
♪ <i>I've been comin' up short</i> ♪

00:43.215 --> 00:46.176
♪ <i>Just a little too long</i> ♪

00:48.929 --> 00:51.848
♪ <i>Forty hours</i>
<i>Of a dull routine</i> ♪

00:52.474 --> 00:58.021
♪ <i>I've been wastin' my life it seems</i>
<i>And comin' up short</i> ♪

00:58.188 --> 01:00.732
♪ <i>Just a little too long</i> ♪♪

01:00.732 --> 01:02.276
COACH:
Come on, come on, come on!

01:03.235 --> 01:04.319
All right. Go on!

01:04.903 --> 01:06.154
Come on, take it out.

01:06.154 --> 01:07.990
GUS:
I got it.

01:11.994 --> 01:14.329
You want Tobik to finish it off
for you, Gus?

01:14.496 --> 01:16.081
No, I'm fine.

01:16.248 --> 01:20.627
Just need to get out of this inning
and then get a little breather.

01:23.171 --> 01:24.631
Hey.

01:26.341 --> 01:27.467
Hey nothing.

01:31.346 --> 01:32.681
♪ <i>I'm comin' back</i> ♪

01:33.348 --> 01:37.060
♪ <i>This time</i>
<i>I'm comin' up stronger</i> ♪

01:37.936 --> 01:40.063
♪ <i>I been lookin' up</i> ♪

01:40.814 --> 01:44.026
♪ <i>From a long way down</i> ♪

01:45.485 --> 01:47.362
♪ <i>I been lookin' up</i> ♪

01:47.988 --> 01:51.950
♪ <i>From a long way down</i> ♪♪

01:53.577 --> 01:58.081
That ball is tagged.
It's going, going nowhere.

01:59.499 --> 02:01.043
Hold on just a minute.

02:01.209 --> 02:02.878
Let me see that ball.

02:03.045 --> 02:06.298
- What?
- You heard me. Let me see it.

02:09.050 --> 02:12.387
- Frozen ball, Gus?
- Where'd that come from?

02:12.554 --> 02:15.932
You shouldn't have to resort to this.
I mean, where's your pride?

02:16.099 --> 02:19.061
You know, damn,
I searched high and low, and I

02:19.061 --> 02:20.562
I'll have to throw you out.

02:20.729 --> 02:23.857
Come on, Mick.
I'm five outs from finishing this.

02:23.857 --> 02:25.275
Sorry, but you gotta go.

02:25.275 --> 02:28.278
You are gone. You are out of here!

02:28.278 --> 02:29.613
KID:
Mick, come on!

02:30.489 --> 02:31.990
[♪♪♪]

02:34.409 --> 02:36.703
Better not hold on
to that too long, Mick.

02:36.870 --> 02:41.124
If it freezes, they'll have to cut your
fingers off to get rid of the damn thing.

02:45.545 --> 02:48.632
Someone get me a bucket of water!
Get me some water, now!

02:49.299 --> 02:52.719
♪ <i>This town ain't big</i>
<i>This town ain't small</i> ♪

02:52.719 --> 02:55.472
♪ <i>It's a little of both they say</i> ♪♪

02:57.766 --> 03:01.186
That arm numb yet,
or is it in that tingly burning stage

03:01.353 --> 03:03.313
just before everything freezes?

03:03.480 --> 03:06.441
Well, look what the cat drug in.

03:06.608 --> 03:09.194
Don't act like
you're not surprised to see me.

03:09.361 --> 03:12.781
Picked up a whiff of your cologne
about a half an hour ago.

03:13.115 --> 03:15.158
Would you look at these fancy duds?

03:15.158 --> 03:16.618
Flatterer.

03:17.577 --> 03:20.497
Bullshitterer. Hey.

03:20.664 --> 03:21.707
How you doing?

03:22.290 --> 03:24.543
Sorry I missed it.

03:24.793 --> 03:26.461
How'd you throw?

03:26.628 --> 03:27.921
Pretty good.

03:28.088 --> 03:29.673
I moved the ball around a lot.

03:29.840 --> 03:31.758
Even blew a few fastballs by them.

03:34.720 --> 03:35.721
MAN:
I'm okay to drive.

03:35.887 --> 03:38.890
I know you are but you're too drunk
to walk to your car

03:39.057 --> 03:42.644
-so this taxi driver will give you a lift.
- How you doing, bud? Come on.

03:43.311 --> 03:45.939
- Strong and capable woman.
- You left out independent.

03:46.106 --> 03:48.442
Uh-oh. You must be smitten.

03:49.818 --> 03:52.446
Went past smitten a long time ago.

03:52.612 --> 03:55.907
First time in my life,
the woman I love and the woman I like

03:56.074 --> 03:59.786
-happen to be the same person.
- That's a dangerous combo.

03:59.953 --> 04:01.204
And the kicker is

04:01.830 --> 04:05.125
she loves me
but she's not desperate for me.

04:05.125 --> 04:07.377
Which could only mean

04:07.544 --> 04:09.379
you're desperate for her.

04:09.546 --> 04:10.922
You got it.

04:10.922 --> 04:14.050
Yeah, well, six marriages
had to teach me something, huh?

04:14.217 --> 04:15.343
[CHUCKLES]

04:15.802 --> 04:17.596
You ever think about getting out?

04:17.762 --> 04:21.391
As a matter of fact, this is my last season.
I'm hanging it up.

04:21.558 --> 04:23.935
- Oh, yeah? What are you gonna do?
- Yeah.

04:24.102 --> 04:27.105
I don't know. I'm still kicking
a few ideas around.

04:27.606 --> 04:31.026
Well, it just so happens
that I've got a proposition for you.

04:31.193 --> 04:35.030
I thought you came all this way because
you missed the sound of my voice.

04:35.197 --> 04:37.616
- Oh, there is that, but...
- Heh, heh.

04:38.575 --> 04:41.077
Gus, I wanted to ask you,
how would you like to manage?

04:41.661 --> 04:42.871
Manage?

04:43.038 --> 04:46.416
I got a Triple-A team.
A heap of talent, not a baseball player.

04:46.583 --> 04:49.586
What I need, what they need,
is a genuine baseball man

04:49.753 --> 04:51.797
someone who really knows
the game.

04:51.963 --> 04:55.258
With all you know about baseball,
and their natural ability

04:55.425 --> 04:57.135
it'd be a perfect match.

04:57.844 --> 04:58.929
I don't know, Rog.

04:59.095 --> 05:03.350
I mean, uh, I spent the better part of my life
kicking around the minor leagues.

05:03.517 --> 05:05.393
Hell, my ass has gone flat

05:05.560 --> 05:08.313
from sitting on hard benches
and riding bad buses.

05:08.480 --> 05:10.982
I ain't sure in signing up
for more of the same.

05:11.149 --> 05:14.402
But this is something that you know.
Something you could be good at.

05:14.986 --> 05:18.073
Who says I can't be good at something
other than baseball?

05:18.406 --> 05:19.533
No one.

05:21.409 --> 05:23.078
Look, thanks.

05:24.120 --> 05:25.580
Anyway, I--

05:26.414 --> 05:29.835
I come the end of the season, I'm quitting.
Cold turkey.

05:30.252 --> 05:32.754
Hey, I know how to take no
for an answer

05:32.921 --> 05:36.550
but maybe you could do me
one little favor.

05:37.634 --> 05:38.885
If I can.

05:38.885 --> 05:41.847
I'd like you to take a look
at Mr. Downtown Anderson.

05:42.264 --> 05:45.058
- He is a pure hitter.
- Uh-huh.

05:45.058 --> 05:47.143
You got the day off tomorrow, right?

05:47.310 --> 05:50.939
The three of us, why don't
we go down, and watch the kid play?

05:51.106 --> 05:52.941
I'm in.

05:53.733 --> 05:56.611
GUS:
So it's either wrestle me for the ball

05:56.611 --> 05:57.737
or let me stay in.

05:57.904 --> 05:59.447
- So he let you stay in?
- Yeah.

05:59.614 --> 06:00.949
Two dogs and two cokes.

06:01.116 --> 06:04.286
Oh, just ketchup and mustard on mine.
Thanks.

06:04.452 --> 06:06.788
Do my eyes deceive me?

06:06.955 --> 06:08.456
Is that who I think it is?

06:08.623 --> 06:12.294
Slick guy, overdressed,
helmet hair, shit-eating grin?

06:12.878 --> 06:14.170
[♪♪♪]

06:14.170 --> 06:15.630
MAN 1:
Here you go, sir.

06:15.630 --> 06:16.715
MAN 2:
Thank you.

06:16.882 --> 06:19.342
You must have eyes
in the back of your head.

06:19.342 --> 06:23.305
Leonard Huff. Manager
slash bullshit artist extraordinaire.

06:24.431 --> 06:27.517
I know a broken down old ballplayer
when I see one.

06:27.684 --> 06:30.186
- No offense, of course.
- Hey, Huff.

06:30.353 --> 06:31.980
Gus.

06:33.273 --> 06:35.817
Whoa, ho-ho.

06:36.109 --> 06:39.988
And who is this lovely little lady?

06:40.155 --> 06:41.615
I'm Maggie Reynolds.

06:41.615 --> 06:44.576
- Maggie.
- Okay, that's four bucks.

06:44.743 --> 06:45.994
- Thanks.
- I'll get those.

06:46.161 --> 06:47.746
- I got it. It's all right.
- No.

06:47.913 --> 06:50.123
Save your money.

06:50.540 --> 06:52.918
- I got it right here.
- Here we go.

06:53.084 --> 06:54.127
Yes, sir. Out of 10.

06:54.294 --> 06:57.213
Oh, the change is yours, my friend.

06:57.213 --> 06:59.633
Whoa. Thank you, sir.

06:59.799 --> 07:03.637
So, Maggie, Maggie,
are you a baseball fan?

07:03.637 --> 07:05.889
As a matter of fact, I am.

07:06.056 --> 07:09.184
Well, I manage a team.

07:09.351 --> 07:11.269
Minnesota Twins.

07:11.436 --> 07:12.854
Maybe you've heard of them.

07:13.021 --> 07:14.814
The Minnesota Twins.

07:14.981 --> 07:17.943
Maybe I've heard of them,
you asshole.

07:17.943 --> 07:19.569
PLAYER:
Coming down!

07:21.863 --> 07:23.865
Yep. First class all the way.

07:24.032 --> 07:26.493
That's how we do it on the big team.

07:26.993 --> 07:31.164
If he says big team one more time,
I'll pinch his neck until his head pops off.

07:31.331 --> 07:35.001
- The kid I'm talking about.
MAN: <i>Coming to the plate, number one,</i>

07:35.001 --> 07:38.838
Billy "Downtown" Anderson.
Number one in your heart,

07:39.005 --> 07:42.258
<i>-number one in the program. Anderson.</i>
- Play ball!

07:42.884 --> 07:44.678
Downtown!

07:45.220 --> 07:47.013
[♪♪♪]

07:47.973 --> 07:49.683
[CROWD CHEERING]

07:52.519 --> 07:53.895
You like this kid, huh?

07:57.190 --> 07:59.401
PLAYER 1: Yeah.
PLAYER 2:Yeah!

08:06.866 --> 08:08.535
UMPIRE:
Safe!

08:19.004 --> 08:22.340
Super. It is just super.

08:22.507 --> 08:26.720
I was just telling Mr. Downtown here
he's gonna be with the big team soon.

08:26.886 --> 08:28.263
No question about it.

08:28.430 --> 08:30.807
The sooner the better
as far as I'm concerned.

08:30.974 --> 08:34.686
- What do you think, Gus?
- I think he's got a real nice bat.

08:36.563 --> 08:40.607
Well, they say that I've got a pure swing,
that I'm a natural.

08:40.607 --> 08:41.900
Yeah?

08:42.068 --> 08:45.530
Soon as you get over that lack
of confidence, the sky's the limit.

08:45.697 --> 08:47.198
Good game. Get in the shower.

08:47.365 --> 08:50.493
- I don't want my player catching a cold.
- Yes, sir.

08:51.995 --> 08:53.788
Wait a sec.

08:54.789 --> 08:56.833
Gus Cantrell.

08:57.542 --> 09:01.296
Six-one, 185 pounds.
Throws right, bats right.

09:01.463 --> 09:02.547
Yeah.

09:02.714 --> 09:06.426
Yeah, I had triples of your rookie card
when I was in grade school.

09:07.177 --> 09:08.720
You still got them?

09:09.054 --> 09:12.348
I traded them all for one player
to be named at a later date.

09:14.726 --> 09:17.896
I'm kidding. Ha, ha. See you.

09:18.563 --> 09:20.607
Smart ass.

09:24.402 --> 09:26.529
Well, I gotta roll.

09:26.696 --> 09:29.032
- I gotta get back--
- To the big team, huh?

09:29.199 --> 09:31.076
Exactly.

09:33.244 --> 09:34.871
Margaret.

09:35.038 --> 09:36.581
- Nice meeting you.
- Mm.

09:39.375 --> 09:42.295
You ever get tired of the minor leagues,
give me a call.

09:42.462 --> 09:44.339
Just kidding.

09:45.715 --> 09:47.050
No, seriously. Kidding!

09:47.842 --> 09:49.511
Kidding.

09:49.803 --> 09:51.179
All right.

09:51.346 --> 09:52.764
Let's go.

09:52.931 --> 09:54.641
To the airport, my friend.

09:54.808 --> 09:57.477
Oh, hey, listen, keep me posted
on that kid, will you?

09:58.228 --> 10:02.190
Let's go. Airport! Big tip for you.

10:02.357 --> 10:04.776
Like a vulture circling fresh meat.

10:04.943 --> 10:07.862
Yep! Well, he wants Downtown.

10:08.029 --> 10:09.364
He's not gonna wait.

10:09.531 --> 10:12.283
Trust me. He'll wanna bring him up
before he's ready.

10:12.450 --> 10:16.621
You see, that's what I've been saying.
You know how to bring a player along.

10:16.788 --> 10:19.124
A need a manager
with that kind of touch

10:19.290 --> 10:21.751
that kind of instinct.

10:22.252 --> 10:24.295
I want you to take this kid
to Triple-A.

10:24.462 --> 10:27.423
- I want you to teach him.
- It sounds like a lot of work.

10:27.590 --> 10:29.425
Look, try it for a couple of weeks.

10:29.592 --> 10:33.096
You don't like it, no harm, no foul.
You quit.

10:34.013 --> 10:35.598
I need to think about it.

10:35.598 --> 10:39.227
Gus, I need a coach.

10:40.603 --> 10:42.230
Let you know in the morning?

10:43.064 --> 10:44.774
You're on.

10:45.233 --> 10:47.068
[♪♪♪]

10:50.405 --> 10:53.241
- What if I hate it?
- You quit.

10:53.408 --> 10:55.493
He even gave you an out.

10:57.120 --> 10:58.496
Are you scared?

10:58.496 --> 10:59.998
No.

11:02.458 --> 11:04.002
Yeah.

11:05.003 --> 11:08.923
You can't let fear of the unknown
keep you from moving off the dime.

11:11.009 --> 11:12.677
No, really. I mean, what if--?

11:12.844 --> 11:15.972
What if Christopher Columbus
had let fear get in the way?

11:16.890 --> 11:18.766
I'd be playing cricket?

11:18.933 --> 11:21.394
You know what I'm saying.

11:22.437 --> 11:25.023
You really think I could manage
a baseball team?

11:25.190 --> 11:26.482
I know you can.

11:30.195 --> 11:32.572
And what about us?

11:34.157 --> 11:36.034
Us will be here.

11:36.034 --> 11:38.369
Us isn't gonna go anywhere.

11:46.878 --> 11:48.213
[♪♪♪]

11:48.213 --> 11:49.214
[HORN HONKS]

11:57.305 --> 11:59.432
You must be Gus Cantrell.

12:00.099 --> 12:01.809
What gave me away?

12:01.809 --> 12:04.812
Frank Morgan. Everybody calls me Pops.
I'll grab these.

12:04.979 --> 12:07.023
- Thanks.
- Come on. Jump in.

12:08.191 --> 12:09.234
This is Mr. Buzz.

12:09.400 --> 12:11.152
- How you doing?
- Nice to meet you.

12:11.319 --> 12:14.239
We're an hour from game time,
so I brought your uniform.

12:14.405 --> 12:17.951
- Okay.
- We'll move Mr. Buzz's head up here.

12:19.285 --> 12:21.955
Excuse me. Watch your...

12:24.123 --> 12:26.042
You must be pretty excited, huh?

12:26.209 --> 12:27.877
Oh, yeah.

12:45.728 --> 12:47.855
This is the clubhouse.

12:51.651 --> 12:54.779
In some parts of the world,
this is called a basement.

12:54.946 --> 12:58.950
The good news is it's cool in August.
Other times, it can be a little musty.

12:59.117 --> 13:02.287
- Dank?
- That too, but cool.

13:03.162 --> 13:05.123
Here's your office.

13:13.840 --> 13:16.384
Another prayer unanswered.

13:17.510 --> 13:19.095
[♪♪♪]

13:21.973 --> 13:25.685
[HUFFING]

13:25.685 --> 13:29.355
Lance Pere. This is Gus Cantrell,
our new skipper.

13:29.355 --> 13:31.899
Welcome to our unique little troop.

13:31.899 --> 13:33.318
Thanks.

13:33.484 --> 13:36.154
You aren't stuck or anything, are you?

13:36.154 --> 13:39.365
No. It's yoga.

13:39.782 --> 13:43.745
A limber mind leads to a limber spine,
which leads to a long life.

13:43.745 --> 13:46.789
As we go, so goes the world,

13:46.789 --> 13:49.751
for we are the world, the world is us.

13:49.917 --> 13:52.462
I'll have to jot that down.

13:53.755 --> 13:57.675
You better unwind and get dressed,
unless you're planning on playing naked.

13:57.842 --> 13:59.802
Oh. All right, Pops.

13:59.802 --> 14:00.845
[♪♪♪]

14:01.304 --> 14:04.265
Came to baseball
by way of the New York City Ballet.

14:04.432 --> 14:06.601
- Ballet?
- Went to an open tryout.

14:06.768 --> 14:09.103
He's such a natural athlete,
they signed him.

14:09.270 --> 14:11.105
He used to be a ballerina?

14:11.272 --> 14:13.274
I don't think guys are ballerinas.

14:13.441 --> 14:15.818
- Balladeer?
- Don't balladeers sing?

14:15.985 --> 14:17.320
That's a troubadour.

14:17.487 --> 14:19.822
MAN 1:
All right, that's it! That's it!

14:21.574 --> 14:22.825
MAN 2: Go!
- All right.

14:22.992 --> 14:25.036
That was me. I was out of position.

14:25.203 --> 14:27.914
Hog Ellis, this is our new skipper,
Gus Cantrell.

14:28.081 --> 14:29.624
Hey.

14:31.417 --> 14:33.211
What's up?

14:36.047 --> 14:37.840
Nice to meet you.

14:38.424 --> 14:40.676
Hog, show the skipper your fastball.

14:47.016 --> 14:48.017
[GRUNTS]

14:49.519 --> 14:51.145
You got some velocity there.

14:51.562 --> 14:53.356
Yeah.

14:54.107 --> 14:56.067
You can bet on the hummer, baby.

14:56.234 --> 14:57.777
It's all good.

15:01.114 --> 15:04.742
Well, don't let me interrupt.

15:05.410 --> 15:07.161
It's cool.

15:11.916 --> 15:14.293
"Cool" is the only thing he said
I understood.

15:14.460 --> 15:16.129
Hog ain't much on communication.

15:16.295 --> 15:18.756
Remind me not to sit next to him
on road trips.

15:22.468 --> 15:24.178
Gus Cantrell.

15:24.345 --> 15:26.180
- Remember me?
- Rube Baker.

15:26.347 --> 15:29.434
What are you doing here?
I thought you were with San Diego.

15:29.600 --> 15:30.726
I was with San Diego.

15:30.893 --> 15:33.563
Old control problem came
creeping back to haunt me.

15:33.729 --> 15:37.150
- Trouble making the throw to second?
- Yeah. Second.

15:38.192 --> 15:39.944
And first.

15:40.486 --> 15:41.612
Third, a little.

15:42.572 --> 15:46.576
And I still have trouble
getting it back to the pitcher.

15:46.909 --> 15:48.828
Well, come on. I don't believe that.

15:48.995 --> 15:51.873
Just take a deep breath,
rear back, and let it rip.

15:52.039 --> 15:53.583
Okay.

15:58.588 --> 16:00.756
[GLASS SHATTERS, THEN CAR ALARM BLARES]

16:00.756 --> 16:03.009
BOY:
Mom, they did it again!

16:03.176 --> 16:05.470
See what I mean? I just

16:05.470 --> 16:08.473
Well, you're a little bit off the mark,
but don't worry.

16:08.639 --> 16:12.602
- We'll get you straightened out.
- Okay. You want me to go get that?

16:12.602 --> 16:15.146
Don't worry about it.
Keep warming them up.

16:15.146 --> 16:18.024
- Good seeing you, Rube.
- It was good seeing you, Gus.

16:18.191 --> 16:19.567
You got any more balls?

16:19.567 --> 16:23.905
MAN: Yes, sir, I remember Gus Cantrell
from the old California Double-A league.

16:23.905 --> 16:27.074
That was before Diet Coke
became my beverage of choice.

16:27.241 --> 16:30.495
Gus was a fair pitcher,
but he'll have to be more than fair

16:30.661 --> 16:33.498
to turn this bunch into anything
that resembles a baseball team.

16:33.664 --> 16:35.333
- Oh, yeah.
- They suck.

16:35.833 --> 16:37.293
[CHATTERING]

16:38.252 --> 16:40.046
[♪♪♪]

16:44.759 --> 16:46.552
MAN:
Perplexed?

16:46.552 --> 16:50.431
Carlton Windgate, pitcher.
Everyone, calls me Doc.

16:50.431 --> 16:54.602
Gus Cantrell, manager.
Everybody calls me Gus.

16:54.602 --> 16:57.271
Oh, I'm delighted
to make your acquaintance.

16:57.438 --> 16:58.481
Yeah.

16:58.648 --> 17:00.483
Likewise.

17:01.025 --> 17:04.654
So you have a question
regarding the scorecard or?

17:05.363 --> 17:08.031
As a matter of fact,
there's seems to be a mistake.

17:08.199 --> 17:11.160
You got Juan Lopez at second
and Juan Lopez at short.

17:11.327 --> 17:13.996
That's no mistake. Juan!

17:13.996 --> 17:15.957
- Oh, shit.
- Hello, coach.

17:16.123 --> 17:17.458
Buenos dias.

17:19.544 --> 17:21.420
- Brothers?
- Twins.

17:21.587 --> 17:25.090
- With the same name?
- Confounding, is it not?

17:25.633 --> 17:28.344
Confounding seems to be
the word of the day.

17:28.511 --> 17:31.597
Listen, from now on,
you're gonna be Juan 1.

17:31.764 --> 17:33.558
<i>- Si.</i> Okay.
- You're gonna be Juan 2.

17:33.724 --> 17:35.101
- Sounds good, coach.
- Okay.

17:35.268 --> 17:38.688
Excuse me, but by numbering them

17:38.854 --> 17:43.067
you risk stifling their identities
and squelching their self-esteem.

17:45.611 --> 17:50.074
I don't wanna be rude here, Doc,
but how would you like to be Juan 3?

17:53.494 --> 17:54.996
[♪♪♪]

17:55.621 --> 17:57.415
MAN:
Batter up!

17:58.666 --> 18:00.668
♪ <i>Baby, baby, baby, baby, baby</i> ♪

18:01.210 --> 18:03.087
♪ <i>Baby, baby, baby, baby, baby</i> ♪

18:03.838 --> 18:05.089
♪ <i>Baby-baby, baby-baby</i> ♪♪

18:05.756 --> 18:07.633
Watch out!

18:08.884 --> 18:12.179
PLAYER: Get your glasses, catcher!
- All right, Rube. Good job, Rube.

18:13.931 --> 18:17.310
So a routine throw
becomes a 2-base throwing error.

18:17.476 --> 18:20.271
Mr. Buzz almost got nailed
by that missile.

18:20.438 --> 18:23.566
And we all might be better off
had he got nailed.

18:26.277 --> 18:27.570
[GRUNTS]

18:29.363 --> 18:30.323
[CROWD BOOS]

18:35.077 --> 18:37.371
All right, Lance! Shake it off, buddy!

18:37.538 --> 18:39.790
Shake it off. Get the next one, bud.

18:39.790 --> 18:42.126
Lance the Dance
had a slippery one that time.

18:42.293 --> 18:44.795
They don't call him Old Stone Hands
for nothing.

18:44.962 --> 18:47.048
I've seen better hands on a clock. Heh, heh.

18:49.008 --> 18:51.927
Juan 1 has the ball,
still time to make the throw.

18:51.927 --> 18:54.472
No, Juan 2 has the ball!
Hey, wait a second!

18:54.472 --> 18:56.265
- A brawl!
- What are you doing?

18:56.265 --> 18:57.683
Oh, here we go again.

18:57.850 --> 18:59.977
Come on, cut it out, you guys!

19:00.394 --> 19:04.065
DOYLE: The brothers Lopez are going at it.
Juan 2 looks hurt.

19:04.065 --> 19:07.443
No! Here he comes fighting back!
He connects with a right!

19:07.943 --> 19:10.071
- What a shot!
POPS: Stop it! Stop it!

19:10.071 --> 19:12.281
You can't play ball! I'll kill you!

19:12.281 --> 19:14.367
- You're ugly!
- It's an error.

19:14.367 --> 19:16.410
- You! You!
POPS: Come on, cut it out.

19:16.410 --> 19:18.788
UMPIRE:
You're both out of here!

19:18.788 --> 19:21.791
So all Juan Lopez is concerned
get the heave-ho

19:21.957 --> 19:25.211
and right about now,
Gus Cantrell has gotta be wondering

19:25.378 --> 19:26.879
why he ever took this job.

19:27.046 --> 19:31.342
You know, fans, it's games like this
that used to get me overmedicated.

19:32.385 --> 19:34.011
[♪♪♪]

19:41.477 --> 19:45.106
Keep hitting them up the middle,
all right? They'll catch on.

19:51.612 --> 19:53.489
He got a bad jump on that one.

19:53.656 --> 19:56.951
Not only that, he ran too long
in the same spot.

20:01.831 --> 20:03.249
[RADAR GUN BEEPING]

20:03.249 --> 20:05.543
Huh. Couldn't get a reading.

20:06.794 --> 20:10.256
Got that from the Highway Department.
It doesn't pick up under 55.

20:10.423 --> 20:13.467
- Under 55?
- How was that, coach?

20:14.552 --> 20:16.303
- It was good, Doc.
- Excellent.

20:16.470 --> 20:18.305
You wanna see my change-up?

20:18.472 --> 20:19.640
No, no. I'm good.

20:19.640 --> 20:22.476
- Super. We'll stay with the heater.
GUS: That-a-baby.

20:25.771 --> 20:29.191
GUS: Lance Romance. Coach?
Let me see your mitt.

20:31.777 --> 20:33.612
Try this for a while.

20:35.823 --> 20:37.783
Hey, I can't field with this.

20:37.783 --> 20:40.619
I hate to tell you,
you ain't hot with a glove either.

20:40.786 --> 20:43.748
- Yeah--
- I want you to get used to feeling the ball.

20:43.748 --> 20:46.709
Loosen up those hands a little bit.

20:48.043 --> 20:49.295
Okay, coach.

20:57.011 --> 20:59.096
Go ahead, open it up.

21:04.185 --> 21:06.103
It's a first baseman's mitt.

21:06.270 --> 21:09.398
That's what the guy
at the sporting goods store said it was.

21:09.565 --> 21:13.486
I'm no first baseman. I'm an outfielder.
Been an outfielder all my life.

21:13.486 --> 21:16.071
I know you're an outfielder, Pops.

21:17.156 --> 21:20.367
- It might be better for the team if we--
- Hold on now.

21:20.367 --> 21:22.536
I've been around a long time.

21:22.703 --> 21:26.457
Don't give me the-best
for-the-team speech. I'll take it straight.

21:26.624 --> 21:30.044
You're too old, you're too fat,
and you're too slow.

21:30.211 --> 21:31.504
Straight enough?

21:35.508 --> 21:37.468
Yeah. That'll do it.

21:37.468 --> 21:39.261
But I like your bat.

21:39.428 --> 21:42.473
And I need a leader on the field,
I think you're my man.

21:43.432 --> 21:45.351
So...

21:45.643 --> 21:48.771
what do you say?
You wanna give first base a shot?

21:49.563 --> 21:53.984
Sure. I'm-- If you think
that's best for the team.

21:54.527 --> 21:55.861
Thanks, Pops.

21:56.445 --> 21:57.696
Yeah.

21:58.239 --> 22:00.658
[♪♪♪]

22:02.785 --> 22:06.121
Okay, so pure hitter now,
what's that mean?

22:06.288 --> 22:10.584
See, I got these naturally
quick hands, you know?

22:10.751 --> 22:13.212
Yeah, I got a pretty good eye too.

22:13.379 --> 22:15.047
No, no, no.

22:15.214 --> 22:16.632
Nicoise.

22:16.799 --> 22:19.718
I told you. We got ranch, Italian,
chunky blue cheese,

22:19.885 --> 22:22.847
-which is 50 cents extra.
- Okay.

22:23.347 --> 22:25.891
Do you have any balsamic vinegar?

22:26.308 --> 22:27.977
I got ranch, Italian,

22:28.143 --> 22:31.021
-chunky blue cheese.
- Okay.

22:31.021 --> 22:33.190
You know what? Forget the salad.

22:33.357 --> 22:36.986
Bring me a gun,
and I'll just shoot myself, okay?

22:38.863 --> 22:42.449
Pops, I was wondering, you?

22:42.658 --> 22:44.827
You ever make it to the show?

22:45.619 --> 22:47.204
- Came close once.
- Yeah?

22:47.580 --> 22:51.083
With the Red Sox organization.

22:51.250 --> 22:54.628
It was in October. A player got injured.
I got the call.

22:55.087 --> 23:00.009
And I was on the plane flying into Boston
when a freak snowstorm hit.

23:00.009 --> 23:01.969
We couldn't land.

23:02.428 --> 23:05.973
Two days later, weather's fine,
so is the player.

23:06.640 --> 23:09.768
No way. That was it?

23:09.768 --> 23:12.688
Twenty years, professional baseball,
I circled the show.

23:12.855 --> 23:14.648
Couldn't land.

23:15.858 --> 23:18.319
Windgate, you'd call
a finesse pitcher.

23:18.319 --> 23:20.321
Moves the ball up and down,
in and out.

23:20.487 --> 23:22.865
Relies on control and savvy.

23:23.282 --> 23:27.161
They time this kid's fastball
with an hourglass.

23:27.578 --> 23:29.246
[♪♪♪]

23:36.587 --> 23:37.880
[BONES CRACK, THEN GRUNTS]

23:48.682 --> 23:50.559
Anderson.

23:54.730 --> 23:56.857
Sacrifice him over.

23:57.274 --> 24:00.653
- Sacrifice?
- Bunt him over into scoring position.

24:00.653 --> 24:02.112
You're kidding me.

24:02.112 --> 24:05.199
No, I'm not kidding. Lay one down.

24:05.366 --> 24:07.409
BOY:
Hit one, Downtown!

24:07.576 --> 24:08.869
Okay.

24:19.296 --> 24:20.923
MAN:
D.T.!

24:22.216 --> 24:23.634
[CHEERING]

24:23.634 --> 24:28.555
Anderson drives one to left and deep.
Hey, get up, get out of here, gone!

24:28.555 --> 24:32.768
For Anderson and the Buzz
lead this game 3 to 2.

24:32.768 --> 24:34.311
Good job, buddy.

24:34.478 --> 24:36.397
- D.T.!
- D.T.!

24:41.527 --> 24:43.112
ALL:
Yeah.

24:44.989 --> 24:46.824
PLAYER:
D.T.

24:50.786 --> 24:52.079
We got it, baby!

24:52.246 --> 24:53.956
- That was an extreme shot.
- Food.

24:54.123 --> 24:56.542
- Let's-- Anderson.
- I want some food, baby.

24:56.709 --> 24:58.627
Roast beef sandwich.
I want cheese.

24:58.794 --> 25:02.047
Bologna, some turkey,
some potato salad, a pickle.

25:02.214 --> 25:05.092
Anderson. Anderson.

25:05.259 --> 25:07.052
I need to see you.

25:08.554 --> 25:10.848
PLAYER 1: Someone's in trouble.
PLAYER 2: Doesn't look good.

25:11.015 --> 25:14.268
- If I'm not back in five minutes--
PLAYER 3: Put the sandwich to go.

25:14.560 --> 25:17.312
PLAYER 1: All right, you guys.
PLAYER 2: Just make him his sandwich.

25:18.564 --> 25:20.024
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

25:20.024 --> 25:22.234
- Yeah.
- Hi.

25:22.818 --> 25:23.944
Pull up a chair.

25:29.575 --> 25:33.662
See, this ain't the Downtown show,

25:33.829 --> 25:38.125
so when I ask you to lay one down,
you lay one down.

25:40.252 --> 25:42.046
But I won the game.

25:42.046 --> 25:43.547
Well, that's not the point.

25:43.714 --> 25:45.049
We're a team here.

25:45.215 --> 25:47.009
We do what's best for the team.

25:47.176 --> 25:48.927
And I make that decision.

25:49.094 --> 25:52.014
This isn't about one guy
doing what he wants to do.

25:52.014 --> 25:57.311
- Even if that one guy wins a ball game?
- Even if that one guy wins a ball game.

25:58.145 --> 25:59.688
Okay.

25:59.855 --> 26:02.357
I'm benching you
for the next three games.

26:05.277 --> 26:07.488
- You're serious?
- Yeah.

26:07.488 --> 26:11.158
I'm on a roll. Had five hits
in my 12 at-bats, and you'll bench me?

26:11.158 --> 26:12.910
Three games, you sit.

26:13.494 --> 26:15.829
- Is that all?
- Yeah, that's it.

26:30.260 --> 26:33.514
- Skipper, can I talk to you for a second?
- Sure. What's up, Doc?

26:33.514 --> 26:35.057
[♪♪♪]

26:35.057 --> 26:38.143
I've been working with Rube,
trying to help him to open up.

26:38.310 --> 26:40.813
- Open up?
- We were breaking down some walls

26:40.979 --> 26:43.524
and I believe
that Rube's throwing problem

26:43.690 --> 26:47.152
goes back to an abrasive
little league coach.

26:47.319 --> 26:51.865
Rube can't throw worth a shit
because of some jerk-off little league coach?

26:52.116 --> 26:53.742
In layman's terms, yes.

26:53.909 --> 26:57.162
And I wanna ask you
if you could just be gentle with him.

26:57.329 --> 27:01.917
See, Rube's psyche is far more delicate
than his rugged facade would indicate.

27:02.084 --> 27:04.503
You want me to give him
my gentle speech?

27:04.670 --> 27:07.047
If you would be so kind.

27:07.047 --> 27:10.425
And, skipper, I wanna thank you
for making yourself accessible

27:10.592 --> 27:12.469
to such an open dialogue.

27:13.095 --> 27:14.930
You bet.

27:16.974 --> 27:20.435
It's strong for your legs.
It'll be good for first base.

27:20.602 --> 27:22.354
- Balance yourself, Pops.
- Okay.

27:22.521 --> 27:26.316
Okay, now we're gonna do jeté.
We're gonna leap like a gazelle.

27:26.483 --> 27:29.736
- Follow me, baby. Whoo.
- Gazelle. Okay.

27:29.736 --> 27:31.613
LANCE:
Leap! Leap!

27:31.613 --> 27:34.575
♪ <i>Taking care of business</i>
<i>Every day</i> ♪♪

27:35.909 --> 27:38.704
Let the ball get further
across the plate, right?

27:38.871 --> 27:43.458
Further in on you, and then hit
the inside half of it right into right field.

27:43.625 --> 27:45.460
You can't help but hit it that way.

27:45.627 --> 27:47.838
Why do I wanna hit it into right field?

27:47.838 --> 27:49.756
- I'm a pull hitter.
- I know you are.

27:49.923 --> 27:53.385
It won't be long
until every pitcher knows it too. Just try it.

28:02.227 --> 28:04.188
All right, try again.

28:04.354 --> 28:06.565
This time, act like you give a shit.

28:15.824 --> 28:18.493
- Hey, Rube.
- Hey, skip.

28:18.660 --> 28:20.162
I've been wondering,

28:20.329 --> 28:23.498
you got any hidden skills?

28:24.082 --> 28:25.459
Hidden skills?

28:25.459 --> 28:29.755
If my car wasn't running right, could
you take the carburetor apart and fix it?

28:30.297 --> 28:33.008
No. No, I don't know nothing
about carburetors.

28:33.425 --> 28:38.013
How about if I bought you some lumber,
could you make me a coffee table?

28:38.639 --> 28:40.807
Nope. Don't believe I could.

28:40.807 --> 28:44.811
So your skills lend themselves
primarily to baseball, we could say that?

28:47.522 --> 28:49.316
Yeah, we could say that.

28:51.652 --> 28:54.780
If another routine throw lands
15 rows in the grandstands,

28:54.947 --> 28:56.949
I'm sending your ass home.

28:57.741 --> 28:59.576
So you better make your throws.

28:59.576 --> 29:02.037
Or I suggest you invest
in some how-to books

29:02.204 --> 29:04.581
and find a fallback profession, understood?

29:04.748 --> 29:06.458
Yeah. Yes, sir.

29:06.667 --> 29:07.709
[♪♪♪]

29:10.420 --> 29:12.297
I'm gonna need this.

29:14.174 --> 29:17.386
I thought you were gonna give him
the gentle speech.

29:17.552 --> 29:19.429
That was it.

29:19.638 --> 29:20.681
[♪♪♪]

29:26.687 --> 29:31.775
God, if you can hear me, please...

29:32.276 --> 29:36.363
send me one real baseball player.

29:36.530 --> 29:38.699
That's all I ask.

29:38.991 --> 29:41.702
And if you can't grant me that,
then, well,

29:41.868 --> 29:44.579
you might as well
just strike me dead

29:44.746 --> 29:46.081
right here and now.

29:49.793 --> 29:50.836
MAN:
Uh-oh.

29:56.508 --> 29:57.926
[♪♪♪]

30:01.972 --> 30:03.098
God?

30:03.682 --> 30:04.891
No.

30:07.019 --> 30:08.186
Moses?

30:08.186 --> 30:10.772
No, but you're getting warm.

30:12.024 --> 30:13.317
Cerrano.

30:16.820 --> 30:17.946
Hello, Gus.

30:19.573 --> 30:23.076
- Oh, Jesus Christ.
- Be careful, now.

30:23.493 --> 30:24.703
You scared me to death.

30:25.287 --> 30:28.332
Do you mean when you realized
God is black?

30:28.498 --> 30:29.624
Yeah.

30:30.375 --> 30:32.753
I thought she was white.

30:35.130 --> 30:38.842
I must've been out a long time
if it's Halloween already.

30:39.009 --> 30:40.177
What's your point?

30:40.177 --> 30:44.598
Pedro Cerrano, the original voodoo man
from Mars, dropped out of baseball

30:44.598 --> 30:47.017
to find whatever the hell it was
he lost.

30:47.184 --> 30:48.393
Maybe his mind.

30:48.852 --> 30:51.480
Anyway, he's back
with a new piece of lumber.

30:51.480 --> 30:53.815
Let's see if he remembers
how to swing it.

30:55.442 --> 30:56.485
Hey, how about that?

30:56.651 --> 30:59.654
Cerrano must have bumped
into the god of all line drives.

30:59.821 --> 31:02.199
He hit a bullet
down the left field line.

31:02.199 --> 31:05.202
Two runs score, and the Buzz
put one in the win column.

31:06.161 --> 31:09.998
- Yeah!
DOYLE: They're on a roll now, baby.

31:10.290 --> 31:12.376
CERRANO:
Piece of love.

31:17.672 --> 31:18.840
Juan!

31:18.840 --> 31:23.053
The Lopez brothers pull off
a double play, 4 to 6 to 3.

31:23.220 --> 31:27.015
Hey, and not a punch was thrown,
not a drop of blood spilled.

31:27.015 --> 31:28.975
All right, Pops, nice stretch.

31:29.142 --> 31:32.562
All right. Nothing like
a little brotherly love.

31:34.064 --> 31:35.732
PLAYER:
Bunt!

31:39.027 --> 31:40.112
Out!

31:42.614 --> 31:45.242
So the Buzz win their third in a row.

32:00.424 --> 32:02.384
Oh, my.

32:02.592 --> 32:04.136
- Cerrano?
- Yo.

32:04.302 --> 32:05.929
Cerrano.

32:06.096 --> 32:08.014
Si, Gus, what?

32:12.352 --> 32:13.895
Is that who I think it is?

32:13.895 --> 32:15.021
[♪♪♪]

32:15.021 --> 32:16.356
[CERRANO SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

32:16.356 --> 32:17.983
CERRANO:
Tanaka.

32:22.070 --> 32:23.155
[IN ENGLISH]

32:33.707 --> 32:35.500
[IN ENGLISH]
Did your part to beautify America.

32:38.378 --> 32:40.589
[IN ENGLISH] I see you've got it
made in the shade, man.

32:46.428 --> 32:48.096
Peace of brain?

32:57.481 --> 32:59.024
Peace of mind.

33:00.567 --> 33:02.903
[IN JAPANESE]

33:03.945 --> 33:05.989
Basically, yeah.

33:06.781 --> 33:11.453
[IN ENGLISH]

33:17.959 --> 33:20.295
[♪♪♪]

33:20.670 --> 33:23.381
Uh, what does your, uh, inner voice tell you?

33:23.757 --> 33:27.093
[IN JAPANESE]

33:27.093 --> 33:29.804
[IN ENGLISH]

33:30.514 --> 33:35.352
Ahh. Sounds like Taka needs a vacation.

33:36.269 --> 33:37.771
I got just the thing.

33:37.938 --> 33:39.898
- Come on.
CERRANO: Watch your step.

33:40.232 --> 33:42.901
[♪♪♪]

33:54.412 --> 33:57.749
WOMAN: Go, Taka.
MAN: Come on, you can do it.

33:59.042 --> 34:02.837
DOYLE: Taka Tanaka, like Cerrano,
left baseball for a while.

34:03.296 --> 34:05.465
Here's the windup and the pitch
to Tanaka.

34:05.632 --> 34:08.467
He swings and lines a single
to right field.

34:08.467 --> 34:10.929
Tanaka hit that one right on the screw.

34:12.639 --> 34:16.184
♪ <i>I'm turning Japanese, I think I'm turning Japanese</i>
<i>I really think so</i> ♪♪

34:18.018 --> 34:20.146
[♪♪♪]

34:21.982 --> 34:24.234
DOYLE:
Holy crapola.

34:24.234 --> 34:26.360
The Buzz just pulled off a double steal.

34:26.527 --> 34:28.737
Either someone got
their signals crossed

34:28.905 --> 34:31.908
or this is starting to look
like a baseball team.

34:43.003 --> 34:44.629
UMPIRE:
Safe.

34:46.130 --> 34:48.174
What is that? What's he doing?

34:48.174 --> 34:52.262
MAN: Bravo.
WEEVILS: I think that's a curtsy?

34:52.429 --> 34:55.806
DOYLE:
Lance Pere is curtsying to the crowd.

34:56.349 --> 34:58.810
Heh. He's blowing kisses and curtsying.

34:58.977 --> 35:01.646
This must go back to his days
as a balladeer.

35:01.646 --> 35:02.939
Oh, he was a singer?

35:03.106 --> 35:05.025
- Dancer.
- Oh.

35:05.233 --> 35:08.069
PLAYER 1: All right, Lance. Proud of you!
PLAYER 2: Yeah.

35:10.196 --> 35:12.657
ANNOUNCER [ON PA]:
<i>Now batting, Carlos Liston.</i>

35:12.824 --> 35:17.746
Baltimore Orioles, eight,
Minnesota Twins, nothing.

35:17.996 --> 35:21.666
Coach, you're doing a fine job,
a real fine job.

35:21.833 --> 35:25.211
Get your heads in the game, okay?

35:25.378 --> 35:27.088
Put the magazines away.

35:27.255 --> 35:29.883
Put the phones away. Bye, mom.

35:31.926 --> 35:33.553
MAN:
Pick it up. Get ahold of one.

35:36.264 --> 35:38.516
Eighteen million over three seasons

35:38.683 --> 35:42.520
and he doesn't even wave the bat
at the ball.

35:43.438 --> 35:45.231
- What?
- Thought you'd like to know.

35:45.398 --> 35:48.485
The Buzz won again.
That puts them in second place.

35:48.652 --> 35:52.447
Really? Maybe I'll take a trip there,
watch somebody who's interested

35:52.614 --> 35:55.825
-in playing baseball.
- Next game is not until Thursday.

35:55.825 --> 35:57.535
They've got two days off.

36:01.498 --> 36:04.626
ROGER [OVER PHONE]: <i>Hey, Gus. I knew</i>
<i>you could turn that bunch into a ball team.</i>

36:04.793 --> 36:08.672
The first couple of weeks were rough,
but we're starting to come together.

36:08.838 --> 36:11.591
<i>You've got days off.
Why don't you hop on a plane</i>

36:11.758 --> 36:14.386
<i>and let me wine and dine you
Minnesota style?</i>

36:14.552 --> 36:15.553
I can't.

36:15.720 --> 36:19.015
I promised Maggie I'd spend
the days off up there with her.

36:19.015 --> 36:21.685
All expenses paid,
first-class trip to Minneapolis.

36:21.851 --> 36:25.563
In fact, my assistant is calling the hotel
as we speak

36:25.730 --> 36:28.942
-booking the presidential suite.
<i>- I don't know, Rog.</i>

36:28.942 --> 36:31.736
By the time we get up there,
we got to come back.

36:31.736 --> 36:35.448
I'll send my jet for you. Very sexy.
Nice vacation for you and Maggie.

36:35.615 --> 36:36.950
<i>Learjet.</i>

36:37.117 --> 36:38.660
Okay.

36:39.035 --> 36:40.787
Okay, you're on.

36:44.040 --> 36:45.709
Yeah.

36:46.292 --> 36:48.169
[♪♪♪]

36:53.049 --> 36:57.637
So, what's the deal with Carlos?

36:57.804 --> 37:01.516
Well, Carlos is in a love fest
with Carlos.

37:01.683 --> 37:03.852
Oh, what about the rest of your team?

37:04.310 --> 37:07.355
One of them wants to be traded
so he can get a more press.

37:07.522 --> 37:11.776
My center fielder is threatening to quit
because he wants to be a male model.

37:11.943 --> 37:14.529
My shortstop and second baseman
aren't speaking

37:14.696 --> 37:16.489
because one of them's got
a bigger contract.

37:16.656 --> 37:19.284
They haven't turned a double play
in over a month.

37:19.451 --> 37:21.786
So out of your 25 players

37:21.953 --> 37:24.539
baseball is a primary concern
for how many?

37:28.293 --> 37:30.378
Fourteen.

37:31.546 --> 37:33.214
Maybe.

37:37.510 --> 37:39.387
[CROWD BOOING]

37:41.973 --> 37:43.391
It's...

37:43.558 --> 37:45.059
Gotta...

37:45.435 --> 37:48.605
Oh, God, I love this team.

37:52.901 --> 37:54.194
What? I like it.

38:01.868 --> 38:04.954
I'll tell you this.
If I had a good short reliever

38:05.121 --> 38:06.915
I could turn this team around.

38:07.081 --> 38:09.459
- In his wildest dreams.
- What's that?

38:09.626 --> 38:11.669
- Nothing.
- No, no.

38:11.836 --> 38:13.755
- Come on, go ahead.
- Gus.

38:15.381 --> 38:19.427
I'm just saying that a short reliever
is not gonna solve your problems.

38:20.303 --> 38:23.097
- Why's that?
- You got no unity.

38:23.264 --> 38:26.059
Every man for himself.
Nobody's playing for the team.

38:26.226 --> 38:29.604
Right. A few bad eggs
who are spoiling it for everyone else.

38:29.604 --> 38:33.233
Well, you see,
when you have major talent

38:33.399 --> 38:36.569
you get major personalities.

38:36.569 --> 38:39.614
Maybe you got too much talent
and not enough team.

38:41.032 --> 38:44.536
See, this game is about nine guys
working as one.

38:44.702 --> 38:47.413
They don't have to be the best guys
who ever lived.

38:47.580 --> 38:49.290
They just gotta work together.

38:49.707 --> 38:50.834
Oh, that's sweet.

38:51.000 --> 38:54.087
That really is. That's-- That's so sweet.

38:54.254 --> 38:56.714
Nine guys working together as one.
Come on, everyone.

38:56.714 --> 38:58.091
Omm.

38:59.342 --> 39:02.846
Rah-rah-rah! I love that. I do. I love that, but...

39:04.806 --> 39:07.475
you're just gonna have to trust me
on this.

39:08.393 --> 39:11.729
- You don't know what you're talking about.
- Is that so?

39:11.729 --> 39:13.648
This might be a good time
to get the check.

39:13.648 --> 39:18.027
Yeah, no, that most definitely is so.
See, let me explain, okay?

39:18.027 --> 39:20.196
There are two kinds of baseball, right?

39:20.363 --> 39:24.617
There's big league
and then there's little league.

39:24.617 --> 39:28.621
And you, my friend,
you are in the latter.

39:28.788 --> 39:31.207
That smells a little bit like a challenge.

39:31.207 --> 39:35.044
Yeah, well, if you're foolhardy enough
to take it as one, yeah, it is.

39:36.170 --> 39:40.884
Any hour, any day, any week,
my guys will be on the field ready to go.

39:40.884 --> 39:42.176
Waiter?

39:42.176 --> 39:44.345
Wait a second. Say what?

39:44.846 --> 39:50.810
You would actually step
onto the same field as my Twins?

39:50.810 --> 39:53.271
- Is there an echo?
- Let me tell you something.

39:53.438 --> 39:57.191
- Don't poke me.
- If you had the first idea--

39:57.191 --> 39:58.902
I said don't poke me.

39:58.902 --> 40:02.906
In fact, if you had any idea of what-- Ow! Ow!

40:03.072 --> 40:06.159
I told you not to poke me,
you loudmouth moron.

40:06.159 --> 40:08.703
You are breaking my finger.

40:08.912 --> 40:09.954
[♪♪♪]

40:10.622 --> 40:12.498
Son of a bitch.

40:14.500 --> 40:15.919
Freak!

40:16.502 --> 40:18.421
- Let go of my finger, you putz.
MAGGIE: Gus.

40:18.588 --> 40:20.757
- Okay--
- Stop.

40:22.342 --> 40:25.136
HUFF:
Watch my hair. Goddamn it.

40:27.513 --> 40:31.434
One minute, you're telling me about
the improved, responsible Gus Cantrell.

40:31.601 --> 40:34.896
The next thing I know,
you're rolling across a barroom floor

40:35.063 --> 40:38.107
-punching, kicking, and biting.
- I didn't bite him.

40:38.274 --> 40:40.026
Besides, it wasn't my fault.

40:41.736 --> 40:44.656
- It wasn't your fault?
- No. Huff asked me to hit him.

40:45.365 --> 40:49.077
Funny. I don't remember hearing him
request a punch in the nose.

40:49.077 --> 40:52.705
It's, like, a secret guy language.

40:52.872 --> 40:55.959
When somebody pokes you
with their finger more than once

40:56.125 --> 40:58.419
they're saying,
"Come on and hit me."

40:58.586 --> 41:01.714
A secret guy language.

41:02.006 --> 41:06.386
I mean, I knew about the handshake
and the decoder ring,

41:06.386 --> 41:09.639
but the language thing is new to me.

41:09.639 --> 41:10.974
[PHONE RINGS]

41:12.433 --> 41:14.018
Hello.

41:14.936 --> 41:17.689
Yeah, he's right here.

41:17.897 --> 41:19.607
[WHISPERS]
It's Roger.

41:27.740 --> 41:30.326
Listen, Rog, I'm really sorry.

41:33.746 --> 41:35.373
Right now?

41:36.624 --> 41:38.209
Okay.

41:39.002 --> 41:40.545
Okay.

41:41.587 --> 41:43.172
On my way.

41:48.302 --> 41:51.305
Good morning, Mr. Cantrell.
Follow me, please.

41:52.932 --> 41:55.977
ROGER: No, that sounds great.
I think that'll work out great.

41:58.062 --> 41:58.938
Uh-huh.

42:03.443 --> 42:05.945
Behind you all the way, sir.

42:06.487 --> 42:10.199
- Thank you.
ROGER: I'll tell him you said that.

42:12.285 --> 42:13.870
Oh, my God.

42:13.870 --> 42:15.538
Okay, gotta go. Talk to you. Bye-bye.

42:16.122 --> 42:17.749
Are you out of your mind?

42:17.749 --> 42:20.334
You're the fifth person to ask me that.

42:20.334 --> 42:23.004
We can't play the Twins.
We're a minor league club.

42:23.171 --> 42:25.923
- You said nine players together.
- I know what I said.

42:26.090 --> 42:29.010
- Don't throw it back at me.
- You don't believe it?

42:29.177 --> 42:31.262
Well, of course I believe it. It's...

42:31.429 --> 42:33.806
- Coffee, sir?
- Yeah.

42:33.973 --> 42:38.728
I just wanted to say that on behalf
of the entire restaurant staff, go Buzz.

42:38.895 --> 42:40.855
Kick ass.

42:41.397 --> 42:43.149
Thanks.

42:44.317 --> 42:47.070
By the way, that was Huff
on the phone just now.

42:47.236 --> 42:49.989
- He thinks you're gonna back out.
- He said that?

42:50.156 --> 42:52.992
Blowing smoke up your butt.
Those were his words.

42:52.992 --> 42:54.827
Gutless. I think he said gutless.

42:54.994 --> 42:58.331
He-- I forgot how he used it.

42:59.165 --> 43:02.043
Big Twins vs. The Little Twins.

43:02.418 --> 43:04.962
Sounds like a good way
to put some butts in the seats, huh?

43:05.671 --> 43:08.925
Do you really think selling tickets
is my sole motivation?

43:12.053 --> 43:14.222
Okay, maybe it is, but nevertheless,

43:14.388 --> 43:18.059
this is a great opportunity for your boys
to see the show up close.

43:18.226 --> 43:21.062
- Gus, come on.
- It's just-- It's dicey.

43:21.062 --> 43:23.564
Why don't you ask your team
what they wanna do?

43:26.234 --> 43:27.485
Huff's finger broken?

43:28.069 --> 43:29.195
Fractured.

43:32.657 --> 43:35.743
Give me 24 hours.
Let me talk to my team.

43:35.743 --> 43:37.120
You're the man.

43:38.246 --> 43:39.163
[PHONE RINGS]

43:39.163 --> 43:40.540
Gotta go.

43:41.040 --> 43:44.043
Hello? Yeah, it's for real.

43:48.047 --> 43:49.757
[♪♪♪]

44:15.408 --> 44:17.326
It's been a while.

44:17.827 --> 44:19.620
One thing never changes.

44:19.787 --> 44:21.330
What's that?

44:21.664 --> 44:23.499
Butterflies.

44:23.833 --> 44:25.376
Yeah.

44:25.877 --> 44:28.504
What a decade to quit drinking.

44:28.504 --> 44:30.423
CARLOS:
Like I said, charges were dropped.

44:30.590 --> 44:33.759
What about your alleged, quote,
"Carlos Liston is so big

44:33.926 --> 44:35.428
he's becoming a religion"?

44:35.595 --> 44:39.182
- I said it. You got a problem with it?
- What exactly does it mean?

44:40.558 --> 44:44.520
It means that people think
of Carlos Liston.

44:44.687 --> 44:47.190
Carlos is on the minds of people.

44:48.983 --> 44:52.445
They pay him respect,
they know him to be a superior man.

44:52.445 --> 44:56.908
Does anyone besides Carlos Liston
worship at the shrine of Carlos Liston?

44:57.074 --> 45:00.286
Or is it a one-man congregation?

45:02.413 --> 45:06.000
Thou shall not make fun of Carlos...

45:06.459 --> 45:09.795
-or thou will get thou's ass whipped.
REPORTER: Oh, my goodness.

45:09.795 --> 45:12.048
- This is unbelievable.
- That's major, man.

45:12.215 --> 45:13.716
We're gonna knock them down.

45:13.883 --> 45:16.135
You'll be like a star.

45:16.135 --> 45:19.138
[SCREAMING]

45:23.726 --> 45:26.062
[♪♪♪]

45:34.820 --> 45:35.863
[GROWLS]

45:38.491 --> 45:42.870
Carlos Liston, resident madman
and cleanup hitter.

45:43.079 --> 45:45.206
- I have to pitch to him?
- Yeah.

45:45.373 --> 45:49.835
Yeah, just remember one thing.
Carlos is a little bit like a mad dog.

45:50.002 --> 45:51.254
Mad dog?

45:51.629 --> 45:56.300
- He smells fear, he goes into attack mode.
- So no matter what you do--

45:56.300 --> 45:58.427
- Don't let him know you're scared.
- Yeah.

45:58.594 --> 46:02.515
- I gotta use the bathroom.
- Use the mound. Stake out your territory.

46:04.225 --> 46:06.852
[♪♪♪]

46:12.817 --> 46:14.151
PLAYER:
Whoo!

46:56.694 --> 46:58.321
Gentlemen.

46:59.280 --> 47:05.786
This is not a should-win
or want-to-win situation.

47:05.786 --> 47:07.872
This is every 8-year-old's dream.

47:08.039 --> 47:11.208
Playing in a big league game
in a big league park.

47:11.208 --> 47:16.047
This is a must-win situation.

47:16.047 --> 47:17.548
Play as well as you can.

47:17.548 --> 47:19.675
I want you...

47:20.676 --> 47:24.597
to humiliate, brutalize.

47:24.597 --> 47:26.307
Don't force.

47:26.682 --> 47:28.517
Don't push, huh?

47:28.517 --> 47:32.897
Beat them into submission.

47:32.897 --> 47:34.899
Let's stay loose.

47:35.441 --> 47:37.318
Let's have some fun.

47:37.651 --> 47:39.737
Come on, guys. What do you say?

47:41.739 --> 47:43.282
[♪♪♪]

47:51.999 --> 47:53.209
Strike three.

47:53.209 --> 47:56.754
He struck him out swinging
and the Hogster is bringing the heat,

47:56.921 --> 48:01.509
throwing gas, tossing aspirins,
blowing smoke, zinging BBs,

48:01.675 --> 48:05.346
firing missiles, zipping darts,
threading the needle.

48:05.513 --> 48:09.683
Let's see if my colleague
in the booth here has anything to add.

48:10.476 --> 48:12.353
Nope, guess not.

48:19.318 --> 48:20.986
Throw. Make your throw.

48:22.029 --> 48:23.280
He got it.

48:32.498 --> 48:33.791
[YELPS]

48:34.834 --> 48:36.419
DOYLE:
Oh, my Lord.

48:36.419 --> 48:38.587
Taka slides safely into first base.

48:38.754 --> 48:41.924
Beautiful and daring.
The only words to describe that play.

48:42.091 --> 48:44.677
Wouldn't you say
beautiful and daring?

48:44.885 --> 48:47.263
Well, my colleague,
a little bashful, concurs.

48:47.430 --> 48:51.809
And this Buzz team has come
to play ball. There's no bout-a-doubt it. Ha, ha.

48:57.314 --> 48:58.816
Got it, baby.

48:59.525 --> 49:01.444
Mine. Mine. Mine.

49:04.905 --> 49:06.615
What the hell?

49:08.117 --> 49:09.743
[♪♪♪]

49:15.082 --> 49:16.917
Keep it up. Keep it up.

49:17.084 --> 49:19.503
Nice, nice, nice. Love to your mother.

49:19.670 --> 49:21.964
Hey, hey, Gussy.

49:22.131 --> 49:24.467
Who the man now? Who the man?

49:25.926 --> 49:27.928
[CROWD CHEERING]

49:28.679 --> 49:30.181
[GRUNTS]

49:32.975 --> 49:34.685
Adams broke up the double play.

49:34.852 --> 49:37.688
Could have been called
for unnecessary roughness.

49:37.855 --> 49:41.025
And that brings Carlos Liston
to the plate.

49:41.442 --> 49:42.443
[♪♪♪]

49:42.443 --> 49:43.527
[CHEERING]

49:44.653 --> 49:46.280
Time out.

49:51.160 --> 49:52.703
Hog.

49:55.122 --> 49:58.751
He's been crowding the plate,
forcing you to throw into his power.

50:01.378 --> 50:03.881
You better give him a little chin music.

50:05.174 --> 50:06.884
You want me to throw at Carlos Liston?

50:07.343 --> 50:09.887
He'll hate you tonight,
but he'll respect you in the morning.

50:13.807 --> 50:15.643
What do I do if he comes out here after me?

50:17.645 --> 50:18.479
Just--

50:18.938 --> 50:21.398
Climbing the center field wall
wouldn't be a bad idea.

50:34.453 --> 50:36.163
DOYLE:
Just calming the kid down.

50:36.163 --> 50:39.291
Probably telling him
to keep the ball down and away.

50:46.966 --> 50:49.051
[♪♪♪]

50:49.051 --> 50:50.594
[CROWD JEERING]

50:51.262 --> 50:54.139
Liston's getting up. He doesn't appear to be hurt.

50:54.139 --> 50:56.350
He doesn't appear to be happy.

50:56.350 --> 50:59.895
Right now would be a good time
to get Hog measured for a casket.

51:08.904 --> 51:10.406
What's up?

51:10.406 --> 51:14.660
Now, I know you ain't throwing at Carlos Liston

51:14.660 --> 51:18.080
because anyone dumb enough to throw at him
wouldn't be smart enough

51:18.080 --> 51:19.957
to find their way to the park.

51:20.541 --> 51:23.544
And you're here, so you ain't that dumb.

51:26.338 --> 51:28.799
I think there was moisture on the ball,

51:28.799 --> 51:31.635
-and it slipped out of my hand.
- Moisture?

51:32.928 --> 51:35.431
Dew. It's a little dew.

51:36.724 --> 51:42.229
Yeah, well, you get that close
to Mr. Liston again, dew or no dew,

51:42.229 --> 51:44.815
and I'll come back and beat you
into the ground with that bat.

51:45.899 --> 51:46.984
You got that?

51:48.235 --> 51:49.695
Yes, sir. Yeah, I got it.

51:49.695 --> 51:50.738
It's no problem.

51:59.788 --> 52:01.790
[CROWD CHEERING]

52:06.503 --> 52:08.505
[♪♪♪]

52:18.432 --> 52:20.726
DOYLE:
<i>A routine fly ball hit to left field.</i>

52:20.726 --> 52:23.771
The wind's got this, taking it back toward the wall.

52:23.771 --> 52:27.232
The wind's gonna carry this one
over the fence for a home run.

52:27.232 --> 52:29.234
[CROWD CHEERING]

52:35.115 --> 52:37.660
I might point out that there is no wind.

52:37.660 --> 52:39.078
We're in a dome.

52:39.078 --> 52:41.205
An enclosed environment.

52:41.205 --> 52:44.083
There's no rain either, in case you were wondering.

52:44.083 --> 52:47.336
Oh, well, excuse me for having an opinion, pal.

52:47.336 --> 52:49.463
- Hey, what's that over there?
- Where?

52:49.463 --> 52:51.882
- Hey!
- Look out.

52:51.882 --> 52:54.510
- Hey, you did that on purpose.
- Look at that.

52:54.510 --> 52:56.261
Oh, my notes.

52:56.261 --> 52:58.472
- My scorecard.
- It was an accident.

52:58.472 --> 52:59.890
- I'm--
- My pants.

52:59.890 --> 53:03.185
Here-- Here-- Here's a 20.
Get yourself another suit.

53:04.186 --> 53:05.229
Oh, wow.

53:07.314 --> 53:09.942
- Come on, Billy.
- Take it out, D.T.

53:10.651 --> 53:13.278
DOYLE:
Some people say Downtown is a big league hitter.

53:13.278 --> 53:16.073
Yeah, he's one of the people spreading that rumor.

53:16.073 --> 53:18.200
I guess now is the moment of truth.

53:19.076 --> 53:21.495
DOYLE:
<i>Here's the windup and the pitch to Downtown.</i>

53:21.495 --> 53:23.580
<i>He swings and drives one to left.</i>

53:23.580 --> 53:26.208
This ball is really hit back toward the wall.

53:26.208 --> 53:29.461
Could get out of here, gone for Downtown.

53:29.461 --> 53:31.922
And the Buzz have tied it at 3 all.

53:31.922 --> 53:33.632
Listen to this crowd.

53:33.632 --> 53:36.218
<i>They love this team.</i>

53:36.218 --> 53:38.220
[CROWD CHEERING]

53:38.804 --> 53:40.806
[WHOOPING]

53:46.145 --> 53:48.480
So much for beating them into submission.

53:48.480 --> 53:49.857
Shut up!

53:55.863 --> 53:57.239
Get the trainer.

53:57.239 --> 53:59.032
Better bring a bag of ice.

54:01.118 --> 54:03.120
[♪♪♪]

54:11.670 --> 54:15.174
Come on, guys. Play a little ball here now. Ah!

54:19.178 --> 54:22.765
DOYLE: <i>Throw by Tanaka heading</i>
<i>towards third. He threw a bullet.</i>

54:22.765 --> 54:25.768
<i>There's gonna be a play
and they've got him! He's out.</i>

54:26.310 --> 54:28.604
What a throw by Tanaka.

54:28.604 --> 54:31.482
- Wasn't that a beaut?
- You're a beaut.

54:31.482 --> 54:33.066
You're finally coming around.

54:33.776 --> 54:36.320
[ORGAN PLAYING "CHARGE"]

54:44.536 --> 54:45.913
CROWD:
Charge!

54:48.373 --> 54:51.210
DOYLE:
Adams swats that one for a single to left field.

54:51.210 --> 54:55.047
Well, slam or swat, the Twins' hitters
have timed this kid's fastball.

54:55.047 --> 54:57.591
Hog will have to go to his other pitches.

54:57.591 --> 54:59.718
- He doesn't have other pitches.
- Does too.

54:59.718 --> 55:02.596
- Does not.
- Does too.

55:02.596 --> 55:03.889
- Doesn't.
- Does too.

55:03.889 --> 55:06.308
- Does not.
- Hey, somebody needs a nap.

55:06.308 --> 55:08.101
He's gonna be sitting on the fastball.

55:08.101 --> 55:10.103
[♪♪♪]

55:10.896 --> 55:12.731
I can't let that happen to Hog.

55:14.650 --> 55:16.026
- Time, ump.
MAN: Time!

55:16.527 --> 55:18.028
- You okay?
- Yeah.

55:20.197 --> 55:21.990
Good job, Hog.

55:21.990 --> 55:25.911
There's nothing to be ashamed of.
We just gotta find you another pitch.

55:25.911 --> 55:27.788
Something to go along with that fastball.

55:30.624 --> 55:31.667
There you go.

55:34.127 --> 55:36.004
- Doc?
- Yep.

55:37.256 --> 55:38.882
Coach, he's got no smoke.

55:38.882 --> 55:41.009
They've been looking at heat all day.

55:41.009 --> 55:42.761
Give them a little change of pace.

55:44.972 --> 55:50.602
ANNOUNCER: <i>Coming to the mound for the Buzz</i>
<i>will be number 35, Doc Windgate.</i>

55:50.602 --> 55:51.979
<i>Windgate.</i>

55:59.486 --> 56:03.156
Well, we got one out left, Doc, but it's a tough one.

56:03.156 --> 56:05.993
You, uh, want me to go with the off-speed stuff?

56:07.661 --> 56:09.413
You-- You got anything else?

56:11.748 --> 56:12.583
Nope.

56:13.834 --> 56:15.586
Let's go with the off-speed stuff.

56:21.258 --> 56:22.634
Let's get this one out.

56:29.266 --> 56:30.934
[♪♪♪]

56:40.652 --> 56:44.656
MAN 1: Yeah, baby!
- That-a-baby, Doc. That-a-baby, Doc.

56:44.656 --> 56:46.033
MAN 2:
Come on, Buzz, go!

56:48.035 --> 56:49.620
WOMAN:
Yeah, Buzz!

56:49.620 --> 56:54.708
Liston swung just a little early...
by about four and a half minutes.

56:54.708 --> 56:56.251
Damn junk baller.

56:56.251 --> 56:59.379
Carlos hasn't seen anything this slow
since high school.

57:08.388 --> 57:11.266
MAN 1: Yeah!
MAN 2: Come on. Come on, Carlos!

57:11.266 --> 57:12.935
That-a-guy, Doc. That-a-guy.

57:12.935 --> 57:14.895
Strike two on Liston.

57:14.895 --> 57:18.398
He's swinging at pitches
that leave Doc's hand on Tuesday.

57:18.398 --> 57:21.026
The trouble is, they don't arrive till Wednesday.

57:27.199 --> 57:28.116
Thanks.

57:28.116 --> 57:30.661
Tell that son of a bitch to throw me his fastball.

57:31.703 --> 57:33.163
That was his fastball.

57:35.958 --> 57:38.043
We're one strike away from extra innings.

57:39.044 --> 57:40.712
If they go up to bat again...

57:41.713 --> 57:43.173
We could lose this damn thing.

57:43.757 --> 57:45.258
- Get this guy.
- All right.

57:45.258 --> 57:48.470
MAN: Let's go, baby.
- One more time. One more time.

57:48.971 --> 57:50.013
I'm gonna kill them.

57:51.515 --> 57:55.018
- You can't do that.
- Oh, look, numb nuts.

57:55.018 --> 58:01.024
This is my ballpark, all right?
I can do anything that I want to.

58:01.024 --> 58:03.777
- You're the manager.
- You're right about that.

58:03.777 --> 58:05.529
You're right about that.

58:13.662 --> 58:17.082
Do it! That's right, I said, kill them.

58:17.082 --> 58:18.375
Here's the pitch.

58:25.882 --> 58:28.135
HUFF:
Oh, isn't that a shame?

58:28.135 --> 58:29.928
[HUFF LAUGHS]

58:29.928 --> 58:31.930
[BAND PLAYING "OYE COMO VA"]

58:33.557 --> 58:36.852
Power outage, my large white buttocks.

58:36.852 --> 58:38.520
Well, that's what he said.

58:39.604 --> 58:43.316
Did you know that Huff has born-to-lie tattooed
on his forearm?

58:44.735 --> 58:45.861
Is that true?

58:47.362 --> 58:49.990
He's on the Twins, Carlos Liston.

58:49.990 --> 58:52.784
Gigantic. You wouldn't believe it if you saw him.

58:52.784 --> 58:55.620
He said, "I'll beat you into the ground with this bat."

58:55.620 --> 58:56.872
What did you say?

58:57.330 --> 59:02.586
I said, you better chase it on back
to the plate where you belong

59:02.586 --> 59:05.672
before I rip your face off
and shove it in your ass. Rear.

59:05.672 --> 59:06.673
Your rear.

59:08.216 --> 59:09.718
- No way.
- Yeah.

59:09.718 --> 59:11.553
What did he do?

59:11.553 --> 59:14.848
He, uh, walked his self on back to the plate.

59:17.976 --> 59:19.311
WOMAN:
Wow.

59:19.311 --> 59:21.354
Tell you what, Rube.

59:21.354 --> 59:23.982
Played a major league team
in a major league stadium.

59:23.982 --> 59:26.318
Made the whole 20 years worthwhile.

59:26.318 --> 59:28.737
- It's a beautiful thing.
- Oh, yeah.

59:31.448 --> 59:33.325
[BOTH SINGING IN SPANISH]

01:00:04.606 --> 01:00:07.484
"They're calling it a tie,
but the Twins were outplayed

01:00:07.484 --> 01:00:09.402
by a younger, gutsy Buzz team.

01:00:09.402 --> 01:00:11.154
Leonard Huff was outcoached

01:00:11.154 --> 01:00:14.699
-by ex-player, rookie manager Gus Cantrell.
- Mm-hm.

01:00:14.699 --> 01:00:17.994
However, a generator snafu allowed
the Twins to limp home

01:00:17.994 --> 01:00:22.124
-with their dignity just barely intact."
- Hmm.

01:00:22.124 --> 01:00:25.001
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

01:00:25.001 --> 01:00:27.879
People are very impressed.
It's made me wondering

01:00:27.879 --> 01:00:30.632
if I didn't have a couple of people in Triple-A

01:00:30.632 --> 01:00:33.343
who were ready to come up to the bigs
and vice versa.

01:00:33.343 --> 01:00:35.595
It did? It made you wonder?

01:00:35.595 --> 01:00:37.139
Yeah, it did.

01:00:37.139 --> 01:00:39.808
Apparently, I'm not the only one who's wondering.

01:00:40.851 --> 01:00:42.269
I got a call this morning.

01:00:43.645 --> 01:00:44.479
Yeah?

01:00:45.147 --> 01:00:48.066
Yeah. Huff, he, uh...

01:00:48.066 --> 01:00:49.192
He wants Downtown.

01:00:51.736 --> 01:00:54.739
- Roger, Downtown's not ready.
- Huff says he is.

01:00:54.739 --> 01:00:57.409
Huff doesn't know his butt from a manhole cover.

01:00:57.409 --> 01:00:59.244
- Gus, listen.
- No, you listen.

01:00:59.828 --> 01:01:02.080
Take Downtown up early,
you may have to send him back.

01:01:02.080 --> 01:01:04.040
That could hurt the kid.

01:01:04.040 --> 01:01:06.293
- Gus--
- He's got a big career ahead of him,

01:01:06.293 --> 01:01:08.920
but you've got to bring him along.
He's just starting to listen.

01:01:08.920 --> 01:01:10.881
- Gus, Gus!
- You take him away from me now--

01:01:13.842 --> 01:01:15.385
Huff is the Twins' manager.

01:01:15.385 --> 01:01:18.972
If he wants to bring a ballplayer
to the show, then I'm sorry.

01:01:18.972 --> 01:01:20.765
He's made it very clear.

01:01:20.765 --> 01:01:22.309
He wants Downtown.

01:01:23.852 --> 01:01:26.730
MAN 1: Have fun, huh?
MAN 2: Stay in touch, brother.

01:01:27.147 --> 01:01:30.066
- Take care, man.
- You guys do too.

01:01:30.066 --> 01:01:31.568
Hey, good luck, bud.

01:01:31.568 --> 01:01:33.069
MAN 3: Good game.
MAN 4: Yeah!

01:01:36.990 --> 01:01:39.284
Well, going to the show.

01:01:39.284 --> 01:01:43.246
Yeah, I'm going to the show.

01:01:44.915 --> 01:01:49.085
Could I make sort of an off-the-wall suggestion?

01:01:49.085 --> 01:01:49.961
Sure.

01:01:51.004 --> 01:01:54.758
Tell Huff you want four more weeks with me
before you go up.

01:01:54.758 --> 01:01:57.052
Convince him you need a little more time.

01:01:58.637 --> 01:02:00.430
What the hell would I want to do that for?

01:02:02.057 --> 01:02:03.558
Because you're not ready yet, kid.

01:02:04.893 --> 01:02:09.898
- Bullshit. Huff says I am.
- Huff doesn't know, okay?

01:02:09.898 --> 01:02:12.400
He's not about turning you into a player.

01:02:12.400 --> 01:02:15.987
He's trying to use a publicity stunt
to cover up a lousy season.

01:02:18.323 --> 01:02:21.201
You know, I knew this. I knew this would happen.

01:02:21.201 --> 01:02:23.662
You'd come in and try to rain on my parade.

01:02:23.662 --> 01:02:25.664
- I'm not trying to rain--
- You are.

01:02:25.664 --> 01:02:27.916
You've been on me since the beginning.

01:02:27.916 --> 01:02:30.252
I hit a home run and you benched me.

01:02:30.252 --> 01:02:33.046
You told me not to pull
when I'm a natural pull hitter.

01:02:33.046 --> 01:02:36.299
- I'm trying to help.
- Don't tell me you are. You're not.

01:02:36.299 --> 01:02:37.592
You never were.

01:02:39.052 --> 01:02:40.553
You want me to tell you why?

01:02:41.596 --> 01:02:43.682
Because you're jealous.

01:02:43.682 --> 01:02:46.518
You're jealous I got more talent on my worst day

01:02:46.518 --> 01:02:48.478
than you've had in your whole goddamn career.

01:02:53.316 --> 01:02:55.735
What, it's true, isn't it? Isn't it?

01:02:55.735 --> 01:02:57.988
Isn't it? You've never had half the talent that I do.

01:03:00.490 --> 01:03:01.700
That's true.

01:03:01.700 --> 01:03:05.453
God, I should have known you couldn't
just shake my hand and say good luck.

01:03:07.455 --> 01:03:10.125
But I don't give a shit because I just passed you up.

01:03:11.126 --> 01:03:14.587
I don't need you, Gus Cantrell.
I'm moving on to bigger and better things.

01:03:16.715 --> 01:03:18.425
Thanks.

01:03:18.425 --> 01:03:19.426
Thanks for nothing.

01:03:22.512 --> 01:03:24.306
Strike two!

01:03:24.306 --> 01:03:25.515
[CROWD JEERING]

01:03:27.183 --> 01:03:28.435
Piece of cake. Piece of cake.

01:03:38.445 --> 01:03:40.071
[CROWD JEERING]

01:03:40.905 --> 01:03:43.700
DOYLE:
<i>So the Buzz lose another close one.</i>

01:03:43.700 --> 01:03:47.329
[ON RADIO] <i>They've dropped seven</i>
<i>of the last eight, making this a rough trip.</i>

01:03:47.329 --> 01:03:48.288
Gentlemen.

01:03:51.082 --> 01:03:54.336
Some of you guys might want
to, uh, check your contracts.

01:03:55.628 --> 01:03:57.630
You set there, Rube?

01:03:57.630 --> 01:03:59.924
- Oh. Yeah, sorry.
- A little more mayo there.

01:03:59.924 --> 01:04:00.800
Okay.

01:04:02.969 --> 01:04:05.347
Seems you signed on to play an entire season,

01:04:05.347 --> 01:04:09.059
but it looks like you quit playing
about two-thirds of the way through

01:04:09.059 --> 01:04:12.354
and I'd like for someone to tell me
what the hell is going on.

01:04:20.487 --> 01:04:21.404
Huh?

01:04:23.698 --> 01:04:24.574
Yeah, Hog?

01:04:26.326 --> 01:04:28.661
Well, you see, um, ahem...

01:04:32.457 --> 01:04:35.293
no one thinks that we can win without Downtown.

01:04:37.295 --> 01:04:38.213
I think.

01:04:38.213 --> 01:04:40.215
[♪♪♪]

01:04:43.134 --> 01:04:45.762
Look, this game is not about one home-run hitter.

01:04:47.055 --> 01:04:50.350
Don't get me wrong. I miss Downtown
as much as any one of you,

01:04:50.350 --> 01:04:52.894
but baseball is not about one player.

01:04:52.894 --> 01:04:57.232
It's about a team, an entire team, playing together.

01:04:58.358 --> 01:05:01.653
That's right. Look at me
like I'm a damn corndog old man

01:05:01.653 --> 01:05:04.155
who doesn't know what the hell I'm talking about.

01:05:05.698 --> 01:05:09.035
You know, I don't, uh, know about the rest of you,

01:05:09.035 --> 01:05:12.080
but I remember not too long ago,
we were the joke of the league.

01:05:12.664 --> 01:05:14.332
Now we've won a few games.

01:05:14.332 --> 01:05:16.876
We even went dead even with the big team,

01:05:16.876 --> 01:05:18.753
and this man made the difference.

01:05:20.797 --> 01:05:23.383
I think we might wanna listen
to what he has to say.

01:05:25.343 --> 01:05:28.513
Look, guys, I'm just asking you to do one thing.

01:05:28.513 --> 01:05:32.142
Start thinking about how you can help
the guy sitting next to you.

01:05:32.142 --> 01:05:34.227
Maybe you know something he doesn't know.

01:05:35.395 --> 01:05:37.897
Maybe you got some information
you can pass along.

01:05:38.773 --> 01:05:41.734
We're traveling tonight.
We got the Crawdads tomorrow.

01:05:41.734 --> 01:05:44.571
By the time we hit the field,
I expect everybody's mind

01:05:44.571 --> 01:05:47.490
to be on teamwork
and the business of baseball.

01:05:49.409 --> 01:05:50.285
Cool?

01:05:52.120 --> 01:05:53.705
It's cool.

01:05:53.705 --> 01:05:55.039
All right.

01:05:55.039 --> 01:05:56.666
Let's pack it up and get out of here.

01:05:57.167 --> 01:05:59.794
- All right, guys.
- See you all tomorrow.

01:05:59.794 --> 01:06:01.796
[♪♪♪]

01:06:05.008 --> 01:06:06.468
It's not complicated.

01:06:06.468 --> 01:06:10.472
A curveball is simply the application
of basic physics.

01:06:12.056 --> 01:06:15.935
Resistance plus velocity equals...?

01:06:19.355 --> 01:06:20.940
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:06:20.940 --> 01:06:22.817
- Uh, motion.
- Bingo.

01:06:22.817 --> 01:06:26.571
Now, by controlling the resistance,
i.e. the rotation,

01:06:26.571 --> 01:06:30.325
you can determine direction of motion.

01:06:30.325 --> 01:06:32.952
And the greater the velocity,

01:06:32.952 --> 01:06:35.788
the less opportunity for--

01:06:35.788 --> 01:06:36.873
[WHISTLES]

01:06:36.873 --> 01:06:38.374
--Resistance.

01:06:38.374 --> 01:06:40.960
Thus, a smaller degree of motion.

01:06:42.337 --> 01:06:43.254
Right.

01:06:43.254 --> 01:06:45.256
[♪♪♪]

01:06:46.257 --> 01:06:48.134
Lesser velocity.

01:06:48.134 --> 01:06:49.761
Create more resistance.

01:06:51.054 --> 01:06:52.597
Allow for greater movement.

01:06:52.597 --> 01:06:54.307
WOMAN:
We love you, Hog!

01:07:00.730 --> 01:07:04.400
- Strike three, you're out!
- He struck him out.

01:07:04.400 --> 01:07:08.154
Hog Ellis has just thrown
the first curveball of his young life.

01:07:08.154 --> 01:07:11.199
And the boy now has not one but two pitches.

01:07:11.991 --> 01:07:14.035
All right. Nice deuce there, Hog.

01:07:14.035 --> 01:07:17.747
I just decreased velocity,
reversed the ball's natural rotation.

01:07:17.747 --> 01:07:20.333
Whatever you say, Hog. Just keep throwing them.

01:07:24.462 --> 01:07:25.713
Way to go, Hogster.

01:07:27.257 --> 01:07:29.092
MAN [ON TV]:
<i>And the count is two and two.</i>

01:07:29.092 --> 01:07:31.177
<i>Norman looks in, gets the signal.</i>

01:07:31.177 --> 01:07:33.680
<i>Here's the pitch. Swing and a miss!</i>

01:07:33.680 --> 01:07:36.683
<i>And strike three. Anderson goes down swinging.</i>

01:07:36.683 --> 01:07:41.104
<i>And is now three-for-15 since joining the Twins.</i>

01:07:44.232 --> 01:07:46.025
Downtown, huh?

01:07:46.025 --> 01:07:48.069
More like down and out, if you ask me.

01:07:52.031 --> 01:07:54.534
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Voodoo! Voodoo! Voodoo!</i>

01:08:02.750 --> 01:08:04.752
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:08:04.752 --> 01:08:08.631
As it's been explained to me,
the hood helps Cerrano focus.

01:08:08.631 --> 01:08:12.260
All I know is, it looks dumb
and he has to be led up to home plate.

01:08:12.260 --> 01:08:15.221
But I've long given up
trying to understand this team.

01:08:20.475 --> 01:08:22.478
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:08:40.078 --> 01:08:42.081
[♪♪♪]

01:08:42.915 --> 01:08:45.126
Cerrano lines a bullet to left center.

01:08:45.126 --> 01:08:47.502
<i>Romance is rounding third.</i>

01:08:57.430 --> 01:08:59.307
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:09:05.020 --> 01:09:08.024
<i>Lance The Dance scores on what appears</i>

01:09:08.024 --> 01:09:11.569
to be a double salchow
and a triple axel thrown in too.

01:09:11.569 --> 01:09:14.529
What a play! The Buzz are back on track.

01:09:14.529 --> 01:09:16.823
<i>They've won seven of their last 10.</i>

01:09:16.823 --> 01:09:18.660
Great job! Come on, baby!

01:09:18.660 --> 01:09:21.996
[IN JAPANESE]

01:09:21.996 --> 01:09:23.581
Now you're having fun, man.

01:09:25.875 --> 01:09:28.252
[CHATTERING]

01:09:31.005 --> 01:09:31.923
You know it!

01:09:31.923 --> 01:09:34.341
[IN JAPANESE]

01:09:36.719 --> 01:09:37.720
All right.

01:09:39.971 --> 01:09:40.807
Hi.

01:09:41.974 --> 01:09:42.809
Hey.

01:09:58.825 --> 01:10:00.284
I couldn't cut the mustard.

01:10:02.787 --> 01:10:03.746
Sorry.

01:10:06.958 --> 01:10:09.252
You can say, "I told you so," if you want.

01:10:09.252 --> 01:10:10.420
No point in that.

01:10:16.884 --> 01:10:19.679
Look, about all that shit I said to you, I'm sorry.

01:10:20.388 --> 01:10:23.683
Well, it's water over the bridge or under the dam,

01:10:23.683 --> 01:10:25.727
or wherever the hell the water goes.

01:10:25.727 --> 01:10:26.811
Sit down.

01:10:26.811 --> 01:10:27.729
Yes, sir.

01:10:31.023 --> 01:10:33.067
Any idea what happened?

01:10:35.987 --> 01:10:37.739
It was, uh...

01:10:37.739 --> 01:10:40.283
I mean, a number of things, really,

01:10:40.283 --> 01:10:43.536
but they started throwing me outside
like you said they would.

01:10:47.915 --> 01:10:49.167
You wanna know the good news?

01:10:50.668 --> 01:10:54.005
Yeah. Yeah, I'd like to hear some good news.

01:10:54.005 --> 01:10:56.215
This is nothing we can't fix.

01:10:56.215 --> 01:10:57.842
Well, how do we do that?

01:10:57.842 --> 01:11:00.845
Sweat, sweat and more sweat.

01:11:01.471 --> 01:11:03.473
[♪♪♪]

01:11:08.478 --> 01:11:11.814
PERE: Straight up with your hands,
straight back with your chests.

01:11:11.814 --> 01:11:13.775
Way back to the sky.

01:11:13.775 --> 01:11:17.195
Way beyond your hands,
and then, back into first position.

01:11:17.195 --> 01:11:18.029
Good.

01:11:20.406 --> 01:11:22.575
[IN ENGLISH]

01:11:32.460 --> 01:11:33.377
CERRANO:
Clear.

01:11:37.048 --> 01:11:39.383
Wow. That's cool.

01:11:44.388 --> 01:11:47.308
- I told you not to do anything fancy.
- If I can get around on an outside--

01:11:47.308 --> 01:11:49.143
Do you know more about hitting than I do?

01:11:49.852 --> 01:11:52.772
- No.
- I'm asking you to do two things.

01:11:52.772 --> 01:11:55.733
Keep your mouth shut and listen to my instructions.

01:11:55.733 --> 01:11:57.276
Can you do that?

01:11:57.276 --> 01:11:58.694
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:11:58.694 --> 01:12:00.112
Okay.

01:12:00.112 --> 01:12:03.074
Don't over swing, all right?

01:12:03.074 --> 01:12:07.119
Take a little bit later and drive it into right field.

01:12:07.119 --> 01:12:08.079
Here we go.

01:12:11.624 --> 01:12:13.251
That's better. That's better.

01:12:13.251 --> 01:12:14.669
CERRANO: You ready?
- Ready.

01:12:14.669 --> 01:12:15.837
It's dark in there.

01:12:18.589 --> 01:12:19.674
You're not scared?

01:12:25.429 --> 01:12:29.016
BAKER: Clear.
- Thinking ball and nothing else.

01:12:29.016 --> 01:12:31.060
BAKER:
Thinking ball and nothing else.

01:12:38.192 --> 01:12:39.735
[♪♪♪]

01:12:39.735 --> 01:12:41.821
♪ <i>Well, I know that it's been a long</i> ♪

01:12:42.446 --> 01:12:44.365
♪ <i>Time since I've been gone</i> ♪

01:12:44.907 --> 01:12:48.995
♪ <i>It's easy to forget or remember</i> ♪♪

01:12:50.037 --> 01:12:51.664
Keep your head down.

01:12:51.664 --> 01:12:54.917
Go, Downtown. Come on, buddy.
Give it a ride. Let's go.

01:12:56.043 --> 01:12:59.213
- Nothing fancy. Keep your head down.
DOYLE: <i>Here's the pitch to Anderson.</i>

01:12:59.213 --> 01:13:03.759
<i>It's a swing and a base hit to right.
This will send Juan 1 to third.</i>

01:13:03.759 --> 01:13:05.720
<i>Downtown's got another base hit,</i>

01:13:05.720 --> 01:13:08.848
<i>sending his average up near the .300 mark.</i>

01:13:08.848 --> 01:13:10.016
MAN:
Safe!

01:13:10.474 --> 01:13:13.352
This kid's not just a home-run swinger anymore.

01:13:13.352 --> 01:13:15.980
He's turning himself into a solid hitter.

01:13:15.980 --> 01:13:17.356
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:13:19.817 --> 01:13:22.361
Coach, you finished the season in first place.

01:13:22.361 --> 01:13:25.072
But, let's face it, you do it without anything

01:13:25.072 --> 01:13:27.575
that even resembles a Major League player.

01:13:27.575 --> 01:13:30.036
Hold it. We got players on this team

01:13:30.036 --> 01:13:33.998
-of Major League caliber.
- Like, uh, who? Downtown Anderson?

01:13:33.998 --> 01:13:35.666
Yeah, for one.

01:13:35.666 --> 01:13:39.337
You know, I heard Coach Huff say
he thinks Downtown's a mistake.

01:13:39.337 --> 01:13:41.130
He even went on to say, I think,

01:13:41.130 --> 01:13:43.466
that he didn't have any business
in the big leagues.

01:13:43.466 --> 01:13:45.468
Once again, Leonard Huff has his head

01:13:45.468 --> 01:13:48.596
shoved up a body cavity
that I can't mention on TV.

01:13:48.596 --> 01:13:50.431
- Excuse me.
- So you disagree

01:13:50.431 --> 01:13:53.017
with Huff's evaluation of Anderson?

01:13:53.017 --> 01:13:54.852
Not only do I disagree

01:13:54.852 --> 01:13:56.979
but I'm not even sure that Huff

01:13:56.979 --> 01:14:00.316
or some of his own players belong
in the major leagues.

01:14:00.316 --> 01:14:01.817
In fact, as far as I'm concerned,

01:14:01.817 --> 01:14:04.779
<i>you're looking at the best team
in the entire Twins organization.</i>

01:14:04.779 --> 01:14:09.492
- Ha! You minor-league peckerwad.
<i>- Beat him man-to-man at every position.</i>

01:14:09.492 --> 01:14:12.870
<i>Once again, though, Huff,
he considers that incomplete.</i>

01:14:12.870 --> 01:14:15.665
<i>- I think he even said...</i>
- I said it was a fluke.

01:14:15.665 --> 01:14:17.833
I wanna hear what he's saying. Shut up.

01:14:17.833 --> 01:14:19.377
- Love this announcer.
- Shut up.

01:14:19.377 --> 01:14:22.380
<i>- The light thing was pretty squirrelly.
- Meaning?</i>

01:14:22.380 --> 01:14:24.632
<i>I'd like to check the fingerprints on that light switch.</i>

01:14:24.632 --> 01:14:26.968
MAN: <i>Are you saying...?</i>
- He's accusing me.

01:14:26.968 --> 01:14:29.845
This son of a bitch is accusing me.

01:14:30.429 --> 01:14:34.934
<i>If we can't beat the Twins,
I'll hand over my entire year's salary to Huff.</i>

01:14:34.934 --> 01:14:37.603
MAN:
<i>And if the Twins lose?</i>

01:14:37.603 --> 01:14:39.522
I can't believe he's doing this.

01:14:39.522 --> 01:14:42.441
<i>The least he could do would be to put up his job.</i>

01:14:43.234 --> 01:14:45.945
<i>So this is a, uh, challenge?</i>

01:14:45.945 --> 01:14:48.364
<i>A friendly challenge with incentives.</i>

01:14:49.865 --> 01:14:52.952
MAN:
<i>If you win, you get to manage the Twins.</i>

01:14:52.952 --> 01:14:55.121
<i>If Huff wins,</i>

01:14:55.121 --> 01:14:57.832
<i>then he takes home your entire year's salary.</i>

01:14:57.832 --> 01:15:01.002
CANTRELL: <i>Right. You know what?</i>
<i>I'm gonna ask for one condition.</i>

01:15:01.002 --> 01:15:03.004
What's that condition gonna be?

01:15:03.004 --> 01:15:07.216
<i>This game should be played at home,
at Buzz Stadium.</i>

01:15:07.216 --> 01:15:11.470
<i>So, Leonard Huff, wherever you are,
the ball's in your court.</i>

01:15:12.680 --> 01:15:16.851
Oh, Jesus, Lenny! You--
You could have just turned it off!

01:15:16.851 --> 01:15:18.602
That son of a bitch set me up.

01:15:18.602 --> 01:15:21.355
He knew every sports channel would run this thing.

01:15:21.355 --> 01:15:24.066
- Nobody ever said he was stupid.
- I'll say it.

01:15:24.066 --> 01:15:26.402
He's stupid. He's stupid, stupid.

01:15:26.402 --> 01:15:28.779
- He's so stupid.
- Oh, stop.

01:15:28.779 --> 01:15:32.324
He's stupid.

01:15:32.324 --> 01:15:33.659
What am I gonna do now?

01:15:34.952 --> 01:15:38.414
You got one of two choices.
You can either play the Buzz

01:15:38.414 --> 01:15:42.626
or you can have the entire world
of baseball call you a coward.

01:15:43.294 --> 01:15:44.295
It's up to you.

01:15:45.629 --> 01:15:49.633
- By the way, you just bought yourself a $1200 TV.
- Mm?

01:15:53.012 --> 01:15:55.014
[♪♪♪]

01:16:06.400 --> 01:16:07.276
HUFF:
Let's go!

01:16:24.210 --> 01:16:27.546
Jobu, what are you doing here?

01:16:27.546 --> 01:16:28.839
I told you before.

01:16:29.882 --> 01:16:33.135
These boys, they've got to do it on their own.

01:16:33.135 --> 01:16:36.347
I would love to use you, but I cannot.

01:16:36.347 --> 01:16:39.600
So, please, get back in the bag.

01:16:46.607 --> 01:16:47.817
But stay close.

01:16:47.817 --> 01:16:49.902
Jesus Christ, what a dump.

01:16:49.902 --> 01:16:52.905
Oh, man, can you imagine living like this?

01:16:52.905 --> 01:16:54.990
- Whoa! Look out! Easy.
- Hey, look out!

01:17:00.454 --> 01:17:01.997
CANTRELL:
Sorry to have to do this,

01:17:02.915 --> 01:17:05.251
but there's a speech clause in my contract.

01:17:05.251 --> 01:17:06.710
[TEAM LAUGHS]

01:17:07.503 --> 01:17:11.549
I know you've all read in the paper
that this game is a publicity stunt.

01:17:11.549 --> 01:17:14.552
Part of my ongoing feud with Leonard Huff.

01:17:15.553 --> 01:17:18.639
But it would be foolish and self-indulgent

01:17:18.639 --> 01:17:24.103
for me to put you all in such a jam,
in such a tough game for publicity.

01:17:24.854 --> 01:17:30.442
No, my motivation is stronger,
deeper than that. It's...

01:17:32.069 --> 01:17:33.237
It's ego.

01:17:33.237 --> 01:17:34.405
[TEAM LAUGHS]

01:17:36.282 --> 01:17:38.659
Unlike some coaches who might ask you

01:17:38.659 --> 01:17:42.538
to play the game because you love it
or because you're fulfilling a dream,

01:17:42.538 --> 01:17:47.710
I'm asking plain and simple
that you win this one for me.

01:17:47.710 --> 01:17:49.211
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:17:49.211 --> 01:17:51.463
Win this one for Gus Cantrell.

01:17:51.463 --> 01:17:54.300
Now, stay loose, play hard. Give it your best shot.

01:17:54.300 --> 01:17:57.469
Let's go out there
and take a bite out of the big team's ass.

01:17:57.469 --> 01:17:59.054
[ALL YELLING]

01:17:59.972 --> 01:18:03.559
CROWD:
♪ Root, root, for the home team ♪

01:18:03.559 --> 01:18:06.854
♪ If they don't win
It's a shame ♪

01:18:06.854 --> 01:18:11.066
♪ 'Cause it's one, two
Three strikes, you're out ♪

01:18:11.066 --> 01:18:15.779
♪ At the old ball game ♪♪

01:18:15.779 --> 01:18:17.781
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:18:21.160 --> 01:18:24.163
WOMAN:
Let's go now! Come on, boys!

01:18:24.163 --> 01:18:25.623
MAN:
Let's go! Play ball!

01:18:27.416 --> 01:18:29.835
Gentlemen, you know the ground rules.

01:18:29.835 --> 01:18:33.172
So let's shake hands.
Have a good, clean ball game.

01:18:33.172 --> 01:18:35.466
MAN:
Let's go! Come on!

01:18:35.466 --> 01:18:36.717
WOMAN:
Play ball!

01:18:39.595 --> 01:18:41.680
I'll give you the beating of your life.

01:18:42.097 --> 01:18:44.725
- We'll see about that.
- Yeah, we will.

01:18:44.725 --> 01:18:45.893
By the way,

01:18:46.644 --> 01:18:50.814
some of the guys have been wondering
where you got your toupee.

01:18:50.814 --> 01:18:52.733
This is not a toupee, all right?

01:18:52.733 --> 01:18:55.569
- This is real.
- You can level with me, huh, Lenny?

01:18:55.569 --> 01:18:57.738
- Come on, where'd you get it?
- It's real.

01:18:57.738 --> 01:18:59.156
- It's mine.
- Come on.

01:18:59.156 --> 01:19:02.201
It is. It's real, and it's mine. See that?

01:19:02.201 --> 01:19:03.994
Dumbass. Ha!

01:19:06.205 --> 01:19:09.250
I'll go, uh, tell the guys they were wrong.

01:19:10.125 --> 01:19:12.127
[CROWD LAUGHING]

01:19:13.671 --> 01:19:15.756
[♪♪♪]

01:19:15.756 --> 01:19:17.967
The first pitch has yet to be thrown

01:19:17.967 --> 01:19:20.886
and already Leonard Huff is tearing his hair out.

01:19:20.886 --> 01:19:23.389
And what a lovely head of hair it is.

01:19:23.389 --> 01:19:26.433
That is, of course, assuming it's real.

01:19:26.433 --> 01:19:29.186
And, frankly, I've always had a question.

01:19:31.146 --> 01:19:33.148
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:19:46.453 --> 01:19:47.413
You're out!

01:19:49.581 --> 01:19:50.916
All right, Lance.

01:19:54.461 --> 01:19:55.671
MAN:
You're out of there!

01:19:57.589 --> 01:20:00.551
What style. What finesse.

01:20:00.551 --> 01:20:05.973
What "je ne sais quoi,"
which is Italian for "what a hell of a play."

01:20:05.973 --> 01:20:09.768
It's French, and it's je ne sais quoi.

01:20:09.768 --> 01:20:12.646
Get out of here.
It means the same thing in French?

01:20:12.646 --> 01:20:14.565
What about that?

01:20:14.565 --> 01:20:15.774
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

01:20:15.774 --> 01:20:17.234
God bless you.

01:20:17.234 --> 01:20:19.153
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Hog! Hog! Hog!</i>

01:20:25.701 --> 01:20:27.619
Strike two!

01:20:30.497 --> 01:20:33.042
Kid learned to throw a curveball, huh?

01:20:33.042 --> 01:20:35.669
Gee, I don't know. Was that a curveball?

01:20:35.669 --> 01:20:37.963
I mean, it's hard for me to tell from way back here.

01:20:42.551 --> 01:20:44.428
DOYLE:
Carlos moves in closer,

01:20:44.428 --> 01:20:47.306
trying to get a good look at Hog's mystery pitch.

01:20:47.306 --> 01:20:50.726
- Otherwise known as a curveball.
- Probably a curveball.

01:20:51.393 --> 01:20:53.979
Carlos is taking the plate away from Hog.

01:20:53.979 --> 01:20:55.939
Kid's afraid to throw him inside.

01:20:55.939 --> 01:20:57.941
<i>Hog! Hog! Hog!</i>

01:21:00.527 --> 01:21:02.988
MAN 1: Come on, man.
MAN 2: Come on.

01:21:06.283 --> 01:21:07.117
MAN 3:
Nice!

01:21:09.578 --> 01:21:10.913
MAN 4:
Come on! Come on!

01:21:13.123 --> 01:21:14.500
MAN 5:
Second. Second.

01:21:17.086 --> 01:21:19.088
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:21:19.088 --> 01:21:22.299
Alrighty, Hog. Come on, buddy.
Hang tough now. Let's go.

01:21:22.299 --> 01:21:24.510
Ha-ha! Let's go. Let's go, guys.

01:21:24.510 --> 01:21:26.345
We need some more runs now.

01:21:26.345 --> 01:21:28.722
Be a hitter up there. Be a hitter up there.

01:21:28.722 --> 01:21:33.227
Hey, hey, pitcher's got a rubber arm.
Ha-ha! Hey, give me some pistachios.

01:21:36.939 --> 01:21:39.900
Hey, that's it. That's it. Go, go, go!

01:21:43.278 --> 01:21:44.738
[CROWD JEERING]

01:21:47.074 --> 01:21:48.450
You're out of there!

01:21:48.450 --> 01:21:50.285
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:21:50.911 --> 01:21:53.122
Good job. Good job.

01:21:53.122 --> 01:21:54.123
CANTRELL:
You all right?

01:21:57.376 --> 01:21:58.836
MAN 1:
Come on, Buzz!

01:22:00.754 --> 01:22:01.839
MAN 2:
You're the man!

01:22:03.507 --> 01:22:04.925
Yeah! Yeah!

01:22:08.303 --> 01:22:09.596
MAN 3:
Two! Two!

01:22:09.596 --> 01:22:11.807
- Come on!
- Come on, baby.

01:22:11.807 --> 01:22:13.809
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:22:16.228 --> 01:22:18.564
DOYLE:
<i>Well, the entire Lopez family scores.</i>

01:22:18.564 --> 01:22:22.568
And the Twins learn the hard way,
you can't pitch around Anderson.

01:22:22.568 --> 01:22:24.361
He's become a complete hitter.

01:22:24.361 --> 01:22:26.321
WOMAN: Come on!
MAN: Come on, Twins!

01:22:26.321 --> 01:22:29.700
All right. Come on, come on.
Let's go. I need some more runs.

01:22:29.700 --> 01:22:31.201
More runs.

01:22:33.162 --> 01:22:35.164
[♪♪♪]

01:22:39.376 --> 01:22:40.836
You're out of there!

01:22:43.672 --> 01:22:46.425
DOYLE:
<i>That's poetry, pure poetry.</i>

01:22:46.425 --> 01:22:52.139
Poe, Wadsworth, Barry Manilow,
Maya Angelou, this Buzz Ball Club.

01:22:52.139 --> 01:22:55.142
What do they all have in common? Poetry.

01:22:55.142 --> 01:22:57.060
And I have to ask my colleague,

01:22:57.060 --> 01:23:01.148
have you ever seen a sunset
more beautiful than that play at the plate?

01:23:02.566 --> 01:23:05.152
My colleague is speechless. He's speechless.

01:23:06.236 --> 01:23:08.363
Come on, let's go! Hey!

01:23:08.363 --> 01:23:12.534
Twinkle toes, go ahead and get a lead.
A little bigger lead. That's it.

01:23:12.534 --> 01:23:14.912
Pitch count. What's the pitch count?

01:23:14.912 --> 01:23:17.831
- Ninety-seven.
- Jeez, you moron. You are killing me!

01:23:17.831 --> 01:23:19.208
And you are not helping.

01:23:20.501 --> 01:23:21.877
Yeah.

01:23:21.877 --> 01:23:23.879
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:23:24.796 --> 01:23:26.715
- All right, all right.
- Come on, Lance.

01:23:27.925 --> 01:23:30.219
- Give me an I!
CROWD: I!

01:23:30.219 --> 01:23:32.304
- Give me an A!
- A!

01:23:32.304 --> 01:23:34.431
- Give me an N!
- N!

01:23:34.431 --> 01:23:36.225
- Give me a C!
- C!

01:23:36.225 --> 01:23:37.976
- Give me an E!
- E!

01:23:37.976 --> 01:23:43.440
- What have you got?
- Lance!

01:23:43.440 --> 01:23:46.109
Top of the ninth. Twins are leading 4 to 3.

01:23:46.109 --> 01:23:48.820
And with two outs and a runner on second,

01:23:48.820 --> 01:23:52.282
the big man, Carlos Liston, comes to the plate.

01:23:52.282 --> 01:23:53.825
Hey, Cantrell!

01:23:53.825 --> 01:23:56.828
Scoreboard!

01:23:56.828 --> 01:23:58.872
Man, you must love these minor leagues.

01:23:58.872 --> 01:24:00.874
[♪♪♪]

01:24:04.836 --> 01:24:09.466
Come on, now! Come on, now!
Hit a one-ton tomato! Ha-ha-ha!

01:24:15.764 --> 01:24:17.266
Yes, yes, yes!

01:24:21.687 --> 01:24:22.813
MAN:
Foul ball!

01:24:22.813 --> 01:24:23.897
Oh, shit!

01:24:26.358 --> 01:24:29.778
That ball lands foul for a very long strike one.

01:24:31.071 --> 01:24:32.322
HUFF:
All right, Carlos!

01:24:32.322 --> 01:24:35.576
Pop one out and I'll give you
all the tamales you can eat! Huh?!

01:24:36.076 --> 01:24:37.411
Keep it fair!

01:24:45.752 --> 01:24:46.920
Yes, yes, yes!

01:24:50.507 --> 01:24:52.676
Ah! Yes! Yeah!

01:24:55.721 --> 01:24:57.014
I better go talk to him.

01:24:57.014 --> 01:24:59.600
Another long strike, and here comes Cantrell.

01:24:59.600 --> 01:25:01.893
And I imagine he's gonna ask Hog Ellis

01:25:01.893 --> 01:25:04.438
to keep some of these strikes inside the park.

01:25:09.776 --> 01:25:10.611
Hey.

01:25:11.778 --> 01:25:13.405
Got two strikes on him.

01:25:13.405 --> 01:25:14.281
Yup.

01:25:15.407 --> 01:25:16.825
They were beauties too, huh?

01:25:17.784 --> 01:25:19.411
He's crowding the plate a little bit.

01:25:23.081 --> 01:25:23.915
Yeah.

01:25:25.250 --> 01:25:26.084
Ho--

01:25:28.086 --> 01:25:29.838
- Hog.
- Yeah.

01:25:29.838 --> 01:25:33.634
You wanna walk him and pitch to the next batter?

01:25:39.556 --> 01:25:40.390
No.

01:25:42.392 --> 01:25:43.435
I want Carlos.

01:25:43.435 --> 01:25:45.437
[♪♪♪]

01:25:47.064 --> 01:25:48.899
It's time for a little chin music.

01:25:50.609 --> 01:25:51.777
You sure?

01:25:51.777 --> 01:25:55.906
Yeah. When he hits the dirt,
you get the ball back to me, quick as you can.

01:25:56.573 --> 01:26:00.118
- All right.
- If he comes out, I'll try to cut him off.

01:26:00.118 --> 01:26:02.913
No, Pops, you stay put.

01:26:05.582 --> 01:26:06.667
This is my fight.

01:26:12.422 --> 01:26:14.424
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:26:19.471 --> 01:26:21.264
CANTRELL:
He's gonna knock him down, boys.

01:26:22.516 --> 01:26:25.185
- He's gonna knock him down.
- Come on, Hog, let's do it, buddy.

01:26:47.332 --> 01:26:48.375
MAN:
Hey there, hold on!

01:26:51.878 --> 01:26:53.922
All right, now, just hold on.

01:26:53.922 --> 01:26:55.507
Wait, wait, wait.

01:26:56.508 --> 01:26:59.136
Now, this here is a hundred-mile-an-hour fastball.

01:26:59.136 --> 01:27:01.304
The most powerful fastball known to man.

01:27:01.722 --> 01:27:05.392
From this distance, if it were to hit you,
it'd take your head clean off.

01:27:06.935 --> 01:27:08.311
Of course, I could miss.

01:27:10.272 --> 01:27:12.524
But my control has been pretty good today.

01:27:14.526 --> 01:27:17.529
So you gotta ask yourself one question.

01:27:19.906 --> 01:27:21.158
Do I feel lucky?

01:27:23.452 --> 01:27:24.286
Well...

01:27:25.996 --> 01:27:27.622
do you, Carlos?

01:27:39.217 --> 01:27:40.761
MAN 1:
Let's go. Play ball.

01:27:40.761 --> 01:27:42.596
MAN 2:
Okay, let's play now!

01:27:42.596 --> 01:27:44.598
WOMAN: Play ball!
MAN 3: Come on!

01:27:44.598 --> 01:27:46.433
MAN 4:
Let's go! Let's go!

01:27:49.102 --> 01:27:50.520
Play ball!

01:27:52.939 --> 01:27:54.983
MAN 5:
Let's take it to him, come on!

01:27:54.983 --> 01:27:56.985
[♪♪♪]

01:28:09.831 --> 01:28:11.416
MAN:
Strike him out!

01:28:11.416 --> 01:28:13.835
Strike three, you're out!

01:28:15.253 --> 01:28:17.672
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:28:17.672 --> 01:28:20.133
Yeah, yeah!

01:28:20.133 --> 01:28:21.218
[WHOOPS]

01:28:22.469 --> 01:28:23.678
Man, you did it!

01:28:24.763 --> 01:28:26.431
Yeah!

01:28:27.891 --> 01:28:28.934
Yeah!

01:28:31.937 --> 01:28:33.021
ELLIS:
Yeah!

01:28:33.939 --> 01:28:35.190
[ELLIS WHOOPS]

01:28:36.233 --> 01:28:37.651
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

01:28:43.573 --> 01:28:45.450
This is bad.

01:28:45.450 --> 01:28:47.160
Very bad. Not good.

01:28:47.160 --> 01:28:49.913
That brings us to the bottom of the ninth.

01:28:49.913 --> 01:28:53.458
By the way, folks, Hog Ellis is not a fighter.

01:28:53.458 --> 01:28:55.877
- For sure.
- I'm guessing he's appealed

01:28:55.877 --> 01:28:58.547
-to Liston's humane side--
- Begging for his life.

01:28:58.547 --> 01:29:00.882
--Explaining we're here to enjoy the game.

01:29:00.882 --> 01:29:03.218
- Speak for yourself.
- There's no reason

01:29:03.218 --> 01:29:05.554
-to get angry or hurt.
- Especially not Hog.

01:29:05.554 --> 01:29:09.391
And let me say this,
if there is a sportsmanship award,

01:29:09.391 --> 01:29:11.726
my vote goes to Hog Ellis.

01:29:11.726 --> 01:29:15.188
And, oh, there's the other half
of the voodoo magic brothers.

01:29:15.188 --> 01:29:16.565
Taka Tanaka.

01:29:17.566 --> 01:29:20.443
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Taka! Taka! Taka!</i>

01:29:20.443 --> 01:29:22.445
[♪♪♪]

01:29:44.926 --> 01:29:48.346
[SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

01:29:48.346 --> 01:29:50.348
You're all nuts. You know that?

01:29:50.348 --> 01:29:52.309
Every last one of you.

01:29:52.309 --> 01:29:55.186
DOYLE:
It's an aura thing, which can only be appreciated

01:29:55.186 --> 01:29:57.314
by those of an enlightened nature.

01:29:57.314 --> 01:30:00.483
Yeah, it doesn't hurt
if you're a little tweaked upstairs.

01:30:00.483 --> 01:30:03.528
Don't even try and tell me
you can see with that thing on.

01:30:03.528 --> 01:30:07.324
DOYLE: Tanaka takes a couple of practice cuts
and steps up to the plate.

